title: jalapeno pie
directions: Grate cheese and set aside.
Bake 2 pie crusts 10 minutes at 350°; remove from oven.
Put 1/2 cheese in each pie shell. Combine eggs, cream, cumin and hot chilies in blender.
Pour over cheese and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wine punch
directions: Add all ingredients into a 2-quart container.
Chill in refrigerator before serving, approximately 2 hours.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and simmer at low heat about 1 hour.
Two pound chickens are recommended.
Quarter or cut into pieces.
Brush pieces thoroughly with sauce.
Place on the grill, turning and brushing every five minutes.
Grill for approximately 20 to 25 minutes depending on size of pieces.
To test for doneness, twist the drumstick if thigh joint moves easily, it is done.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a hole in middle of flour mixture.
Pour oil and milk all at once in hole; mix well. Roll out and make biscuits.
Bake at 450° until golden brown. Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add salt and vanilla.
Add flour and pecans.
Roll in small balls.
Bake for about 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring, until temperature reaches 300°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oil and coloring.
Pour into well-greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and crack.
Cover with powdered sugar by placing in a paper bag and shaking.
Store in airtight container.

title: choco-peanut pumpkin cake
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder,
soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Set
aside.
In
a
large bowl beat eggs; add pumpkin, vegetable oil and bran flakes; mix well.
Add dry mixture and stir
to combine.
Stir in peanuts and chocolate chips.
Pour in a 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients.
Top with mayonnaise; sprinkle with cheese.
Let mixture set in refrigerator for a few hours to marinate.
Top with eggs, bacon and tomatoes before serving.

title: hearty navy bean soup
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and place in large kettle or Dutch oven. Add tomatoes with juice, onion, ham, broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until beans are tender about 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if necessary. Remove ham hock (take meat off of ham hock, if used) and return to soup or leave in ham.
Heat through.
Serves 10.

title: 15 minute apple butter
directions: Cook together apples, sugar and vinegar for 10 minutes.
Add cinnamon drops and cook 5 minutes more.
Pack in hot sterile jars. Makes 5 pints.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost berries.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt into a bowl.
Add berry mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Serve with whipped creamed cheese or butter.

title: molded french cream
directions: Combine sour cream and whipping cream.
Add sugar; beat well. Cook over low heat until warm.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add to cream mixture.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Pour into lightly oiled mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold on platter; garnish with frosted grapes or other fruits.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.

In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, granulated sugar, the 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt. Stir in the milk, oil and vanilla. Stir in the nuts and pour into the prepared baking dish. In a small mixing bowl, stir together the brown sugar and the 1/4 cup of cocoa. Add the boiling water and slowly pour over the batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool on a wire rack and serve warm. Great with a dip of vanilla ice cream while still warm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread pudding - cuban style
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except condensed milk.
Pour into a large baking dish and dribble condensed milk over top.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: hickory nut cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add the egg and vanilla; blend.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 2-inch rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: plain jane casserole
directions: Dilute Cheddar cheese soup with 1/2 can of milk.
Heat in a saucepan.
Add to beans and onion rings.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: red pineapple punch
directions: Stir together all ingredients; serve over ice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and cinnamon in boiling water.
Add cranberry juice cocktail and sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Add orange sections and pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Can be made with sugar-free Jell-O.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, vanilla, brown sugar and eggs. Add flour, salt and soda; mix well. Add by hand oatmeal, walnuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and reaches boil.
Boil 9 to 10 minutes to 238°.
Remove from heat; let stand until it cools to 110°.

title: nut cake
directions: Melt margarine on low flame.
Cream with sugar; mix well.
Add well beaten eggs, then add lemon extract.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add white raisins and pecans.
Add to other mixture. Bake in tube pan lined with 2 layers of brown paper.
Bake for 2 hours at 275°.
Cover with flat piece of foil.
Put pan of water below rack.
When 2 hours is up, remove foil and let brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil, then add raw peanuts.
Boil and stir, when color is nice brown add baking soda and stir fast. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: peggy's cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Butter pan and heat.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, water and lemon juice.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients, mix well (will be coarse and crumbly).
Sprinkle over apples and bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Serve warm with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice and chili casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Season with butter, salt and pepper. Butter 9-inch casserole dish.
Place in layers in this order: rice, sour cream, chilies, Monterey Jack strips.
Spread a top layer with sour cream.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jean's real rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook rice, tomatoes, mushrooms and onions in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir well.
Add wine and seasonings; mix well.
Add broth.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
When rice is tender, add peas and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Pat mixture together for firmness.
Cover with catsup; cook, uncovered, on High for 12 to 14 minutes.
Turn dish every 4 minutes so corners won't burn.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes before serving.

title: meat ball sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until green peppers and onions are done. Add meat balls; heat through.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream
cheese,
mayonnaise
and Ranch dressing; let stand several hours or overnight.
Pinch together the crescent rolls on a pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Let cool; spread cream cheese mixture on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to softened cream cheese; beat well until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over bottom of baked shell; chill.
Combine strawberry gelatin and hot water, stirring until dissolved.
Add strawberries.
Pour over mixture in chilled pie crust.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix softened oleo and cheese spread together.
Then add mayonnaise, garlic powder and seasoned salt together.
Add crab meat.
Spread on English muffin.
Cut with scissors into wedges. Put on cookie sheet; cover with foil and freeze.
When frozen, put wedges in freezer bag and refreeze.
When you want them to serve, put under broiler for 5 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely so they don't burn.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs, juice, cornstarch and sugar.
Bring to boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut marshmallows in fourths.
Fold marshmallows, pineapple and Cool Whip into cooled dressing.
Let set overnight.

title: pretzel jello i
directions: Put 2 cups chopped pretzels in flat baking dish with oleo (melted) and sugar.
Mix all together and bake at 325° for 15 minutes until bubbly.
Let cool.
Next, mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and large Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture over the pretzel crust.
Prepare the jello mix and add the frozen strawberries. Let set and jell until partly set.
Then smooth over the Cool Whip mixture.
This is particularly good when frozen and cut into squares.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Lightly spoon 1 cup flour into measuring cups; level off. Combine the flour with sugar, soda, salt, onions, dill seed and yeast.

title: dad's chicken ole
directions: Bake chicken at 400° for 40 minutes, covered.
Saute onions and pepper, add salsa and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over each chicken breast.
Heat until melted.
Serve with rice and extra salsa.
Don't forget to kiss the cook!

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in medium pot.
Add water, food coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes. Mixture will be globby.
When a ball forms in center of pot, remove to floured surface and knead until it forms a soft dough.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar; add pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake on large jelly roll pan.
Frost with your favorite cream cheese frosting.
Cut into bars.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Minute oats and vanilla. Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Wash and hull the berries and save 3 or perfect ones for garnish.
Puree remaining berries in blender at low speed, then strain to remove seeds.
Sprinkle gelatin over water to soften. Bring 1/4 cup of strained strawberries and sugar to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add remaining puree and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: spaetzles
directions: Mix
eggs,
milk
and
salt
together
and
add
flour. Meanwhile, use a 5 quart
pan filled with water, at least half full; bring water to
a
boil.
Cut
little
spaetzles
with a sharp knife on edge of
bowl
or
use the tip of a tablespoon. Cut into boiling water and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain and add butter or oleo and serve.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine yolks, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt in large saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup milk to form a paste.
Gradually add remaining milk; cook over low heat, stirring frequently until mixture is pudding-like consistency.
Pour into ice cream freezer canister.
Press waxed paper on top of custard.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add cream to cooled custard.
Pack ice cream freezer with cooled custard according to manufacturer's directions.
Freeze according to directions.
Gently mash peaches with 1/4 cup sugar. When ice cream begins to stiffen, add peaches.
Process until finished.
Serve immediately or freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Wash and drain artichokes.
Cut off the stems and the top of each leaf 1/4 of the way down from their tops to remove the stingers.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Sprinkle 2 cups of granola in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Drizzle with topping.
Cut ice cream into 1-inch slices.
Place on granola in pan.
Let stand until slightly softened.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining granola.
Cover and freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Serve with additional, if desired.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add green pepper, celery and onion (chopped) along with the salad oil.
Boil the other ingredients together and pour over beans while hot.
Mix and cool.
Let sit to marinate.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla.
Stir in pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Add raisins and carrots.
Spoon in muffin pans sprayed with vegetable spray.
(Do not use paper liners.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pans. Refrigerate.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash, onions and butter in small amount of water until done and water is cooked out.
Cool and cream thoroughly.
Add well-beaten egg yolks, 1/4 cup crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat lover's lasagna
directions: Combine meat, onion and garlic and brown. Drain off fat. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, basil, sweet basil, oregano, fennel seed, salt and pepper to meat. Simmer for 15 minutes. Set aside. Mix egg, Ricotta, Romano, Asiago, Provolone and Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes together. Set aside. Cook noodles in boiling water for 12 minutes. Drain and lay out on wax paper to cool. In large baking dish, put one layer of noodles, then cheese mixture, then meat mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° until rice is done.

title: carrot and apple salad(gulrot og eple salat)
directions: Combine carrots, apples and lemon juice.
Toss lightly. Chill.
Serve with fish dishes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oyster corn bread pone
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased iron frying pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Recipe from "Island Born and Bread" Cookbook, Harbers Island, North Carolina.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat first three ingredients until gelatin and sugar dissolve. Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese.
Add baby food and pineapple (drained) and set aside to cool.
Add Cool Whip and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish to set.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: night owls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Finely chop nuts.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
(Egg whites may be tinted with food coloring if desired.)
Fold in chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Place in oven. Immediately turn oven off.
Leave oven door shut for 8 hours. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cake cools, stick holes in cake.

title: banana bread
directions: In large bowl add bananas, eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix well. In another bowl combine remaining dry ingredients.
Add mixtures and stir.
Pour into a well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: snappy turtle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening.
Add flavorings.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly. Arrange pecan halves in groups of 3 on greased baking sheet to resemble head and hind legs.
Mold teaspoons of dough into balls. Dip bottoms in egg white and press onto pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost tops.

title: tuna cutlets(prepare the day before)
directions: Cook and stir shortening and flour together. Slowly add milk and cook to a heavy white sauce, adding salt and pepper. Remove from heat and add tuna. Mix well. Pour into a shallow baking dish. Cover and chill overnight.

title: orange date nut bread
directions: Put orange rind and dates or raisins through food chopper and put into mixing bowl.
Then put juice of the orange into a cup and fill up with hot water.
Add soda and pour over dates and orange. Add sugar, oil and beaten egg.
Last, add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced pumpkin fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter, pumpkin and spice.
Bring to a boil and simmer on medium heat, stirring constantly to 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Blend well!
Pour quickly into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. When firm, cut into squares.
Remove from pan.
Pack into box and store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Line baking dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Layer until dish is full.
Top with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; shape into 24 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in oil in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Remove as they brown. Combine soup and broth in Dutch oven.
Add meatballs and vegetables; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer fo 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 large servings.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut celery in 6-inch sticks.
Fill with peanut butter and add raisins on top of peanut butter.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chopped pecans evenly in the bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together in small bowl.
Roll each biscuit piece in sugar mixture.
Place them evenly on top of pecans.
Combine brown sugar and margarine.
Pour evenly over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert onto serving plate. Enjoy!

title: vidalia onion hors d'oeuvre
directions: Boil water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over thin onion rings. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Drain well.
Add mayonnaise and celery seed to taste.
Chill and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: c's refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: (I add mustard seed and dill, fresh or dried.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter. Saute green pepper and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into a covered 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in a large pot; drain and add onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and chips.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls; top with the shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: honey-barbecue flank steak
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey, onion, vinegar, garlic and ginger; pour over meat in glass dish.
Cover; marinate for 12 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Baste with marinade while barbecuing over a hot fire.
Slice in strips on the diagonal. Serve immediately.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Crumble cake up in a large container (punch bowl).
Mix sugar and
softened cream cheese together.
Mix Dream Whip as on package,
then mix with cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cake, then
top
with
pie
filling.
Let set in refrigerator overnight, then serve.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice off top half from dinner rolls.
Spread bottom half with mustard.
Add cheese and ham as if making a sandwich, return top half of rolls.
Mix last four ingredients and pour over "mini sandwiches."
Bake until warm and cheese melts.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Pat one-half of mixture into baking dish.
Pour pie filling over mixture and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly (about 45 to 50 minutes).
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir together until well mixed; drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: warm baguette club sandwich
directions: Slice bread lengthwise, slightly scooping out center.
Spread each half with mustard (and butter/mayonnaise, if desired).
Layer turkey, ham, cheese and tomatoes on bottom half.
Sprinkle with pepper and top with bacon. Place top half of bread on sandwich. Wrap tightly in foil. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Cut into slices. Add lettuce, if desired.
Serve warm.
Excellent with soup, crisp vegetables, corn-on-the-cob and brownies.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hickory nut cookies
directions: One stick margarine may be substituted for butter.

title: little miss muffet broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lo-cal fruit dip(good for diabetics)
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt; blend in until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.
Calories per serving: 100 (4 tablespoon serving).

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in microwave-safe bowl on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil, stirring often, 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Scrape bowl.
Continue microwaving 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions; drain. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion; blend into broccoli. Pour into a buttered casserole baking dish; sprinkle with cheese. In separate bowl, melt margarine and add crumbs.
Mix well; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: creamy beef and macaroni
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni and dressing; heat throughly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add soup, milk and onion.
Heat to simmer.
Slowly stir in Cheez Whiz.
Cook broccoli cuts according to package directions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour hot mixture over broccoli, then stir in Minute rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cook chicken with onion.
Pick off bones; drain broth.
Cook noodles in broth.
Drain noodles; add soup, cheese and chicken. Put in large casserole.
Spread buttered cracker crumbs over top and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: veg all chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss the broccoli, onion, Mozzarella and Swiss cheese and bacon with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar mixture.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in skillet over medium heat.
Stir continually.
When mixture gets to desired brownness pour into pie pan lined with foil and buttered.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Makes 1 small batch.
Great for holiday baskets!

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of pan.
Combine confectioners sugar, eggs and butter.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture on crumbs; sprinkle drained pineapple over the mixture.
Cut up bananas over top.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: country steak
directions: Grease baking dish and flour generously.
Pat one can chuck in bottom of pan and cover with one can undiluted mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 60 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Knead dough; roll into walnut sized balls.
Coat balls with mixture and put into greased Bundt pan.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Grind Oreos in food processor.
In a 13 x 9-inch dish spread 1/2 of the Oreos evenly onto the bottom.
In a large mixing bowl, pour Dream Whip and milk; mix with mixer until fluffy.
Beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Gently pour over Oreos in dish. Spread evenly and sprinkle remaining Oreos over the filling. Resembles top soil.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add butter and egg yolks.
Stir in gradually the buttermilk, vanilla and salt.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Pie should be lightly browned.

title: steam pudding
directions: Steam in double boiler for 2 hours.
Eat warm with milk or fruit.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Put half of bread in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with ham, cheese and remaining bread.
Mix together mustard, eggs, salt and milk and pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 45 minutes.
Top with cornflake crumbles and dot with butter.
Return to oven for an additional 15 minutes.

title: cheesy garlic biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, combine butter, garlic powder and parsley flakes; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and the shortening.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the consistency of cornmeal.
Stir in buttermilk and continue to mix until dough is smooth.
Add cheese and mix well.
(Dough should be soft and pliable.)
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup flour on cutting board surface; turn dough out onto floured surface and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown, brushing butter/garlic mixture over tops of biscuits just as biscuits begin to brown. Serve hot.

title: pot roast platter
directions: Dredge beef in flour.
In large heavy Dutch oven over medium-high heat, brown beef, onions and garlic in butter.
Stir in broth, scraping up browned pan drippings.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Remove to cutting board.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
(At this point, you can freeze meat and pan liquids for later use.)

title: ruiz's specialty oven chicken and linguine
directions: Melt butter in 10 x 15-inch baking pan in a 400° oven, then remove pan from oven.
Stir onion, garlic, basil and pepper into butter.
Place chicken, skin side down, in butter mixture, then turn over.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Place spinach in a 2 to 3 quart casserole dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.
After 15 minutes, break into chunks to speed thawing.
Pour thawed spinach into a colander and squeeze cut liquid.
In a pot of salted boiling water, cook pasta until al dente and drain.
When chicken is done, lift from pan.
Keep warm. Add spinach to pan and stir to scrape browned bits free, then add pasta and cheese.
Mix well.
Season with salt to taste.
Mound a portion of the pasta on each of 4 dinner plates.
Flank with 2 pieces of chicken and an orange wedge.
Before eating, squeeze orange over chicken and pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gran gran's kentucky rice salad
directions: Combine ingredients and toss. Chill thoroughly before serving. Garnish with egg slices.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat a 10-inch skillet with 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry chicken 2 minutes.
Add peppers, onion and cilantro; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in beans.

title: shirley's slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard, water, celery seed and oil together.
Heat and boil this for about 1 minute.
Let this mixture cool.

title: microwave cheese soup
directions: Combine diced potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes; drain and mash.
Add chicken broth, Velveeta cheese, milk, flour and pepper.
Microwave 1/2 power for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Freezes well!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Wash and drain rice; spread out in greased pan.
Cut up chicken and place on rice.
Salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water. Pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil and bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fried cabbage and hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef well and cook onion until tender.
Chop up ground beef well.
Remove ground beef and onion.
Oil skillet; add cabbage.
Cover skillet and stir every 4 to 5 minutes, until slightly browned.
Add all other ingredients; stir.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, peanuts, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix well. Add margarine and mix until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: christmas cheer punch
directions: Bring cider and cinnamon to a boil. Reduce heat and add liquor, stirring until heated. Serve in a tall glass garnished with a cinnamon stick.

title: chocolate fudge turtles
directions: Stir sugar and milk together.
Bring to a gentle boil for 9 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips, butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until blended and chips are melted. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when cold.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter (don't brown much). Add milk and heat (don't boil). Add cheese and all other ingredients.
Add more salt, if desired.
Makes 4 quarts. Can be frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, Velveeta and mushroom soup in glass baking dish. Crumble Ritz crackers and melted butter over broccoli. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes until light brown.

title: shoo fly cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and brown sugar together until fine crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs for topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone it.
Put chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Layer cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix herb dressing, onion, egg and milk.
Mix and pour over soup layer. Pour the chicken broth over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Sprinkle a handful of herb dressing over the top.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, milk, cheese and curry powder to make sauce.
Mix stuffing mix and margarine.
Layer broccoli, then chicken.
Cover with sauce.
Then top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta 4 minutes; drain.
Pour oil, lemon juice and steak seasoning over pasta and let stand for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add olives, pimento and chopped onion; toss and serve.

title: no bake marshmallow rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use wax paper; divide mixture into 5 balls.
Sprinkle coconut on wax paper.
Use hands and press together and roll tight.
Let coconut cover the outside.
Roll each ball into a 10 to 12-inch long roll, then wrap each in the wax paper you used to roll in.
Wrap in foil and freeze until you are ready to use.
Thaw.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: bellini punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl and serve.
This is everyone's favorite.

title: spicy black bean rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour Rotel and beans into casserole dish.
Fill empty Rotel can with uncooked rice and stir into dish. Bake at 350° for about a half-hour or until rice is cooked.
Top with slices or shreds of pepperjack cheese.
Serve on tortillas, as dip with low-fat corn ships or alone as an entree.

title: biscuits for two
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Turn onto floured board; knead 1 minute.
Roll or pat dough in 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 biscuits.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix soup and ground beef, stir well. Add Pizza sauce and noodles. Pour into a large casserole dish, top with mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices. Cover loosely with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer. Makes a very large casserole. Will freeze well.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: oyster cracker treat
directions: Mix dressing, oil and dill weed thoroughly in container with lid.
Add crackers.
Put lid on and toss to cover crackers completely.
Refrigerate overnight for maximum flavor.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add beef; mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat.
Seal edges and ends.
(It looks like a meat loaf; roll like a jelly roll.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: rock cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, ground cloves and allspice.
Then add warm water, pecans and large box raisins. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: matthew's breadsticks
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan at 425°.
Separate biscuits into 10 pieces.
Roll each piece into a long thin snake-shape. Place into pan with melted margarine.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed frog legs
directions: Add salt, pepper and red pepper to frog legs to taste.
Soak frog legs in buttermilk for 8
hours.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter until soft.
Add crab and shrimp meat and cook.
Add crumbled bread to mixture.
Stir in seasoning.
Slit frog legs and put a large spoonful of stuffing in the middle of the frog legs.
Dip this in beaten eggs and roll in corn flour. Fry until golden brown.
You will have to tie each frog leg with a cotton string so stuffing does not come out.
Stuffs approximately 12 frog legs.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Combine the first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast, wheat flour and 1 cup of plain flour to the cracked wheat mixture.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: amber sauce
directions: Bring butter, sugar and syrup to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add cream.
Use to top Amber Crunch squares or as a sundae topping.

title: grandma's chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Blend in butter, sour cream, eggs and vanilla on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Partially thaw the hash brown frozen potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Put on topping of 3 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Put flour in; add buttermilk, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.

title: fruit salad in orange juice
directions: Mix all together using all juices except mandarin oranges.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Rub the cavities of fish with oil, then stuff with ginger and chives.
Bake or steam fish until done.
To serve hot, remove ginger and chives, then fillet.
To serve chilled, refrigerate before removing ginger and chives. Yields 4 servings.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add eggs and cook until firm but not hard, stirring with fork.
Add rice and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook about 10 minutes more.
If dry, add small amount more butter. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vanilla wafer tarts
directions: In cupcake pan, put cupcake papers in each.
Place 1 vanilla wafer cookie in bottom.
Mix other ingredients well and pour atop wafer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and top with cherries or whipped cream.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and nuts.
Moisten with mayonnaise. Add peas.
Mix lightly with 2 forks.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix.
Pour over chicken breasts in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey-mustard chicken breasts(in microwave)
directions: In glass baking dish, place chicken breasts.
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix with honey and mustard.
Pour over breasts. Cover loosely with wax paper.
Cook on High power for 8 to 10 minutes.
Rotate dish halfway.
Cook an additional 4 minutes on High, then check to see if done.
Pepper.

title: hospitality pie
directions: Toast coconut, nuts, and oleo for 15 minutes at 375, stirring. Let cool.
Mix cool whip, Eagle Brand milk, and cream cheese.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut mixture.
Pour caramel over pie and freeze.
Thaw a few minutes before serving. Will keep 2 - 3 weeks in freezer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook until barely tender in salted water the frozen broccoli; drain well and place in shallow casserole.
Combine and blend thoroughly remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over broccoli and mix lightly. Top with homemade buttered bread crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugars and cream until a soft ball forms in cold water, then add nuts, vanilla and butter.
Drop on paper and cool.

title: mexi dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch microwave dish in order given.
Heat until Cheddar is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Moisten sugar with 1/3
cup
of the vinegar.
Add salt, onion and mustard.
Add
remaining vinegar and small amount of oil at a time.
Beat
until mixture is thick.
Add poppy seed. Makes a lot; will keep in refrigerator months.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.

title: incredible pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix.
Add the sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: delicious pickles
directions: Pour off all liquid and slice pickles bread and butter size. Put back in jar.
Over the pickles put the sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Put lid back on and tip so that sugar and vinegar are distributed.
Refrigerate for 3 to 5 days, tipping the jar occasionally, to distribute the juice.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar and flour.
In saucepan, combine water, oil, margarine and cocoa.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool and pour over sugar and flour.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and a dash of salt.
Bake in oblong pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add clams and liquid, canned soup and cubed potatoes.
Simmer until heated through and thin with milk to desired consistency.
Season with pepper.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Add alternately in small portions the flour and drink.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes a very moist pound cake.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
In a casserole dish layer Fritos, ground beef and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beefy mac-n-corn
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, spaghetti sauce, water, pepper and macaroni.
Heat through.
Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Yields 5 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add jam.
Combine flour, spices, salt, raisins and nuts.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Pour in buttered tube pan and cook at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Pour peach juice or any fruit juice over cake.
Ice with caramel icing (recipe in this book).

title: crab meat crisps
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on split muffins.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet until bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pea-cheese salad
directions: Combine in large bowl peas, cheese cubes, chopped eggs, celery, onion and pimiento.
Combine mayonnaise, salt, hot pepper sauce and pepper.
Mix all together.
Slice tomatoes in quarters. Serve over lettuce and tomatoes.

title: ranch-style sausage supper
directions: In a skillet, saute carrots, celery and onion in 2 teaspoons oil.
Drain beans (reserving 1/2 cup liquid).
Add beans, seasonings and bean liquid to skillet with vegetables.
Stir to combine.
Lay sausage on top.
Cover; simmer gently for 10 to 15 minutes to heat sausage through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: erbs biscuits
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix last six ingredients well.
Lay biscuits on top of mixture.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn upside down and serve.
Cook until brown.
Goes with any meal.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift flour and spice together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend 2 teaspoons vanilla into applesauce and add soda, stirring until well mixed.
Blend into first mixture.
Batter will be very stiff.
Stir until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 400° about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa.
Add sugar and milk.
Bring to boil, stirring all the time until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and without removing lid, boil 4 minutes.
Take off cover.
Boil slowly until soft ball is formed when you drop a bit of cooking mixture in a cup of water.
Cool 20 minutes off heat.
Add vanilla, if you wish add peanut butter and/or marshmallow whip.
Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pie tin.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix milk and 1/2 cup tomato sauce in bowl.
Add beaten eggs, onion, sage, salt and pepper.
Soak bread cubes in this mixture and add hamburger.
Mix.
Put in pan and pour remaining tomato sauce over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain. Place in a mixing bowl.

In another bowl, beat eggs, milk and cream cheese. Fold in cottage cheese, sugar, vanilla and spices. Add egg mixture to noodles, mixing well. Add raisins. Pour noodle mixture into a well greased 8-inch square baking dish. Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: irish creme liquor
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apfelbitte
directions: Make dough from above ingredients.
Grate 6 to 8 apples.
Add sugar to taste.
Roll out dough (cold dough).
Place 1/2 dough in pan; prick.
Add apples.
Cover with rest of dough.
Close sides like a pie.
Prick with fork.
Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: beth's tangy chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Melt margarine. Add other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour over chicken breasts and sprinkle each with paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: date nut roll
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in microwave or over low heat. Add dates and nuts.
Spread graham cracker crumbs on sheet of foil or wax paper.
Pour mixture out and make into log, coating with crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Slice thin to serve.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe dish or bowl. Microwave on Medium-high for 1 minute.
Stir, then microwave until mixture is bubbly, stirring as needed.
Use as a dipping sauce for chicken wings or fingers, ham or pork cubes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Brush, wash and skin the mushrooms.
Put the skins to simmer in a little water.
Cut the mushroom caps and stems into very small pieces; add one pint of water and simmer until tender.
Make a sauce of the fat, flour, salt and milk and add the water in which the mushroom caps, stems and skins were cooked.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In skillet, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter or margarine and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil at 250°.
Stir until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Add sweet potatoes; baste with syrup.
Reduce heat to "simmer".
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes. Uncover; cook 10 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pan (9 x 13-inches).
Top with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Layer onions and cheese into dish.
Mix soup and pour over onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Saute beef, celery, onion, pepper, carrot, mushrooms, zucchini, basil and salt.
Then add rice, brown sugar and soup. Cut top off a medium pumpkin; clean out seeds.
Spoon rice mixture into it.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom o's irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add caraway seed.
Cut in butter with knives or pastry blender until mixture is quite crumbly.
Add raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine egg and buttermilk.
Add baking soda to liquid (mixture will bubble slightly).
Quickly stir into dry ingredients until a moist dough is formed.

title: hopped up chicken
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper, rosemary, marjoram and oregano over chicken.
Saute in butter until golden brown.
Add lemon juice and wine.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and orange.
Add sugar.
Prepare jello by quick set method.
When it begins to set, add fruit and nuts.
Mix Well.
Chill until completely set.

title: nutty pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Mix
first
ingredients
together in casserole dish, place bacon slices on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine mixtures.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom only).
Preheat oven to 350°. Put pudding mix in pan; add milk and cook according to package directions.
Place cake mix in large bowl.
Add hot pudding mix to cake mix; stir thoroughly and place in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips along the top of cake, then walnuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, add soup, then pour ketchup and mustard in and season.
Heat through and serve.
Makes a great quick and easy meal.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Marinate overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together dressing, squash, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned on top.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand for taste to develop.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook rice and 2 cups water.
Heat skillet to medium hot.
Add sausage, onions, green peppers and celery.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes to pepper and meat mixture.
Then mix in rice.
Heat, stirring, until all is hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Place butter slices on potatoes.
Put cream of broccoli soup over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Put cheese on top; put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: snickers brownies
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels and 1/3 cup of the condensed milk over hot water.
Set aside and keep warm in large bowl. Combine cake mix, margarine, nuts and 1/3 of the condensed sweet milk.
Mix well, until mixture is combined and crumbly. Press 1/2 of dough evenly into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for about six minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Sprinkle chocolate bits evenly over baked dough and spread caramel mix on top.
Work quickly with broad spatula, crumble remaining half of dough over caramel and press lightly with spoon.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes until top is set.
Cool pan on wire rack 30 minutes.
Then refrigerate until firm (not too long).
Cut into small squares. Makes about 24 brownies.

title: upside apple pecan pie
directions: Note:
Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: spinach lasagna(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, egg, parsley and garlic powder.
Spread 1 cup tomato sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with 4 lasagna noodles, overlapping if necessary.
(Be careful that noodles do not touch outside edges of dish).
Spread 1 cup sauce over noodles.
Layer with 1/3 Ricotta mixture; sprinkle with 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat, layering twice with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer, until browned.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crabmeat won tons
directions: Cut and combine crabmeat and onion in bowl. Add cream cheese. Mix well. Heat oil in pot over medium heat. Take 1 wrapper and add 2 tablespoons of mixture, then roll all corners to middle. Dip finger in water and seal edges. Drop into oil for approximately 2 minutes. Drain on towel.

title: hawaiian punch pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple, Cool Whip, frozen lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add pecans.
Pour over into pie shells.
Let chill for 3 hours in refrigerator.
Slice and serve.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of pan with wafers.
Top wafers with banana slices.
In a large bowl, combine milk and instant pudding. Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes on medium.
Add sweet condensed milk.
Blend with mixer.
Now add tub of Cool Whip. Pour in pan over bananas and wafers.
Top with 5 to 6 crumbled wafers.

title: creole turkey cutlets
directions: Sear cutlets quickly in hot oil, processing in batches if necessary.
Remove.
Quickly saute onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to simmering and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cutlets, spoon sauce over and cover.
Simmer for additional 4 to 8 minutes. Serve with rice or hot buttered noodles.

title: indian chocolate cake
directions: Bring oleo, oil, cocoa and water to a bubbly boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into mixture of flour and sugar.
Add to eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a heavy saucepan.
Separate eggs.
Mix yolks lightly.
Add all the ingredients, except egg whites in with the flour-sugar mixture.
Cook on medium high heat until the mixture is a very thick consistency (as thick as you want the custard to be).
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased skillet. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift plain flour and self-rising flour together.
Add flour to mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well. Add butternut flavoring; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Do not open at all during baking.
Cool in pan and turn out on cake plate.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa and water together.
Add (sifted together) flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Beat well.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sloppy joes(midwest "taverns")
directions: Boil ketchup, water and onion for 3 minutes.
Add ground beef, chili powder and salt.
Boil 7 minutes.
Stir to keep out chunks. Add prepared mustard.
Serve hot in hamburger bun.
Use slotted spoon to fill bun.

title: almond bars (dunking type)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil thoroughly.
Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add almonds last.
If almonds don't stick to dough, add a little water.
Form 3 balls.
Roll the balls into long strips to fit cookie sheet.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Brush each strip with egg wash (1 egg beaten with 1 tablespoon water).
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut cookies at an angle.
Don't toast them. This is an excellent cookie that you will make often.

title: gingerbread upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Add syrup and bring to a boil.
Add pineapple and raisins.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Add molasses and water.
Pour batter over 1st mixture.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes.
Serve with or without cream.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with the syrup of the fruit in a large bowl, then mix in canned fruit.
Stir.
Add sliced bananas and enjoy.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large cooker over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in Rice Krispies cereal until evenly coated.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausages in skillet (first cut into chunks).
Add onion and celery and cook until done.
Place all in Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Add soup, soup mix and rice.
Stir and add water. Check fairly often to see if dry.
If so, add a little more water.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar together. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; make a soft dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in tea size papers in tea size tins.
Bake until lightly brown.
Immediately after removing from oven, press peanut butter cup into center of each cookie until only the top of candy shows.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from tins.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix corn oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend well; add eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla and the dry ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar and roll until all are coated and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 2 or more hours so flavors blend.

title: obazd'n
directions: Cut onions and Camembert in small cubes.
Mix all ingredients and serve on French bread or (if you have) with warm salt pretzels.
This mix should not be liquid.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
In pot, combine all remaining ingredients and stir well.
Add hamburger meat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles(thick, chewy with cracked, sugary tops)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir in.
Chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into balls the size of large walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place, sugared side up, 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle each with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in 3-quart saucepan; add sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.

Mix together Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling. Starting with noodles, layer noodles, sauce and cheese, making sure you have cheese to go on top.
Bake covered with aluminum foil at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove foil, bake for 10 minutes more, until lightly browned.

title: cheese and bacon sticks
directions: Cook bacon until almost done.
Cut 12 strips of bread leaving crusts on.
Put strips of cheese on bread sticks; top with bacon strips.
Broil 5 inches from heat until bacon is crisp.
Makes 12 sticks.
Good with drinks and with soups or salads.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Drain and cut into bite size chunks. Combine soups, eggs, onions, pepper, salt, mayo, 1 1/2 Tbsp. butter and 1 pack of seasoning mix with chicken in a large bowl. Pour 1 pkg. of stuffing mix into greased baking pan, then pour mixture over stuffing. Spread the other stuffing mix on top, then sprinkle the remaining seasoning pack on top of that. Pour remaining butter over top making sure all of the crumbles are moist with butter. You can add more butter, but don't drown in it. Cover dish and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain. Add seasoning and beans.
Warm shells.
Add meat mixture and top meat with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Roll up and place in baking dish sprayed lightly with Pam.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer with salt and pepper.
Debone and reserve water. Saute vegetables in oleo.
Cook spaghetti in seasoned fryer water (about 12 minutes).
Drain.
Add soup, cheese and pimento to vegetables.
Bring to a slow boil.
Pour sauce over chicken spaghetti.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.	Add condensed milk.
Stir until combined.
Add chocolate syrup.
Cook until thick.	Add vanilla. Good served hot on yellow cake, chocolate sundaes.	Will keep in refrigerator for up to 30 days.
You can reheat desired amount in microwave.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Heat liquid
to a boil and dissolve 2 boxes of
gelatin. Fold in berries.
Pour into 9x13 pan.
Chill.
Prepare last box of gelatin in hot water.
Fold in cream cheese.
Cool.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Fold Dream Whip into gelatin mix.
Spread on chilled gelatin.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese and place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook fryer until tender in water with salt and pepper to season.
Drain, bone and cut up chicken; remove fat.
Put chicken, celery, eggs and peas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir soup and broth together.
Pour on chicken mixture; mix all together.

title: apricot filled bars
directions: Place apricots and undrained pineapple in saucepan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar and simmer 5 minutes longer; cool.
Beat butter and 1 cup sugar together.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Gradually add sifted ingredients to butter and sugar, mixing well.
Add nuts and coconut; mix well.
Press 2/3 of this mixture into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread apricot filling over crust.
Crumble remaining coconut mix over all.
Pat down.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
well; add sugar and Karo syrup.
Beat well. Add melted
butter.
Mix flour with pecans and add to mixture. Add vanilla
and beat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a medium oven, about 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from cocktail, pineapple and mandarin oranges. To the fruit, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: lucy's frozen salad
directions: Mix and place in paper muffin cups (in muffin pans).
Freeze.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie mix in pizza pan.
Bake and cool.
Spread cream cheese on large cookie.
Use bananas, pineapple, Mandarin oranges and strawberries to spread on cream cheese.
Ice with strawberry glaze.
Chill.

title: pioneer stew
directions: Cook
ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned
and
vegetables are tender.
Drain all excess fat (if any).
Drain
corn,
beans	and tomatoes.
Add liquids to meat mixture, plus the chili powder and salt.
Cook until liquid is reduced
to
about half.
Add corn, beans and mashed tomatoes. Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until done.
Add 1/2 stick oleo, then cool.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and cheese.
Put in dish.
Mix 1/2 stick oleo with cracker crumbs; put on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spring salad
directions: Stir jello and water well and chill.
Add cottage cheese, celery and onions.
Add mayonnaise and chill until set.
A little lemon juice and horseradish may be added.
Add tomatoes and cucumbers for garnish.

title: pineapple-sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub and boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash, adding butter and undrained pineapple.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth and light.
Stir in 5 tablespoons nuts and turn into buttered casserole.
Bake covered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover; sprinkle with remaining nuts and continue baking for another 10 minutes.

title: asparagus ham quiche
directions: Combine asparagus, ham, cheese and onion and place into two 9-inch pie pans. Mix the other ingredients together, one at a time. Pour over asparagus and ham mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix together. Place in 9 x 13 cake pan, sprayed with Pam or greased a little. Bake at 350° until firm to touch and browned, 35 or 40 minutes.

title: baked cabbage slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 45 to 50 minutes in 325° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crumbs and mix with butter in pan and spread evenly.
Add other ingredients, one at a time.
End up pouring milk over everything.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, 325° for glass pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Stir in syrup.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into chilled unbaked pie crust. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: chimichangas(oven-baked)
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas, butter and cheese, in saucepan.
Simmer until meat liquid is gone (about 5 minutes). Butter one side of tortilla.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of mixture onto center of unbuttered side; top with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Fold 2 sides over filling; fold ends down.
Place seam-side down in 13 x 9 x2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 475° for about 15 minutes, until crisp and golden brown.
Top with guacamole, sour cream, salsa, whatever.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top of pie.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Add soup and cheese, stir until melted.
Put rice in oblong baking dish.
Place broccoli over rice, lay mushrooms over broccoli, then pour soup mixture over rice, broccoli and mushrooms.
Bake for 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: best ever chicken salad
directions: Stew the chicken until done.
Skin, debone and chop into small pieces.
Finely dice the apple, onion and celery.
Add the diced ingredients to the chicken, along with the pineapple in juice. Mix in the mayonnaise (adding a little more, if necessary).
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Nuts and raisins are optional additions.) Best if made the night before.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: impossible pie
directions: Pour everything in blender.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until custard is set.

title: hershey's creamy chocolate cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For crust, in a medium bowl, combine crushed pretzels and 1 tablespoon sugar. Stir in butter.
Press mixture on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake 8 minutes. Cool slightly.

title: italian dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake until mixed.
Pour over salads.
Store rest in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in crescent rolls.
Lay in Pyrex dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over meat and rolls.
Cook at 350° until crescent rolls are brown.

title: scones
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a baking sheet.
Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Add the butter and work with your fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine eggs, cream and vanilla in a bowl and beat until combined.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Flour hands well. Working quickly, lightly put the dough in an 8-inch round.
With a sharp knife, score the round into 8 wedges.
Set on baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes until top is brown.
Serve warm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and sour cream. Cool.

title: sausage puff pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients with egg whites (save yolk for brushing puff pastry).
Spread puff pastry with half of mixture.
Roll like a jelly roll; cut into 15 to 20 pieces.
Repeat with remainder of mixture.
Brush with egg yolk before baking.
If you plan to freeze them, bake first for 15 minutes.
To serve immediately, bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: athean shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen, peel and devein.
In a large saucepan, cook onion, parsley and garlic in 2 tablespoons of butter until onion is tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, oregano and pepper. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Stir in water or Ouzo and fennel.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In pan, cook onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Add chili, corn and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: eggs on horseback
directions: Take the piece of bread and press firmly in the center of a greased cookie sheet.
Square the 4 pieces of cheese around the bread and press firmly in the center to form an indentation. Crack the egg inside and season to taste.
Cook at 325° for approximately 15 minutes.
You can make as many as the family will eat and the kids can help.
A great breakfast treat!

title: red velvet cake 2
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste from cocoa and vinegar.
Add buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Add coloring and cream well.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable wellington
directions: *Puff Pastry sheets available in grocery freezer cases.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
I add a package of taco seasoning.
Cool meat, then add to other ingredients.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar, then eggs (beaten).
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) a little at a time, alternating with mashed bananas.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with soup.
Mix and let set for at least 30 minutes.
Make into small balls.
Fry until done and then drain all grease off.
While meatballs are draining, mix ketchup and jelly in frying pan.
Return meatballs to pan and simmer for five minutes.
Serve in a chafing dish.
After these are made into balls, they can be frozen for a quick snack.

title: spinach-cheddar squares
directions: In medium bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, onion flakes, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and pepper; set aside. Sprinkle bread crumbs evenly onto bottom of lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and spinach. Pour egg mixture evenly over spinach; top with remaining Cheddar cheese and pimentos. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 16 appetizers.

title: hills and humps
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs with electric mixer.
Add flour, 1/3 cup milk and hot butter from pan. Add remaining milk and salt.
Continue to blend with electric mixer.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 20 minutes. Take out of oven.
Pancake will collapse. Cut into squares and serve with warm maple syrup or warmed fruit.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Place pie crust on bottom of a large shallow baking dish and up the sides.
Brown meat, adding seasonings as desired, salt, pepper, garlic powder, seasoned salt, onions, etc.
Drain the meat, then place on pie crust.

title: homemade finger paints
directions: Beat with rotary beater or electric mixer until the volume is tripled.
Divide; add food coloring as desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Freezer paper is good for painting on.
Wet waxy side of paper slightly, then put a spoonful of paint on the paper. Have a wonderful, messy adventure!

title: curried meat and shrimp
directions: Mix bread crumbs, 1/2 cup of onions and chopped beef and form small meat balls.
Saute in oil until brown.
Set aside.
In same skillet, saute in 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine, celery and remainder of onions until soft and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon of oil to same pan and saute shrimp until pink; remove and set aside.

title: tuna sea shell salad
directions: Put all together and add a cup or so of salad dressing or mayonnaise (whichever is preferred).
Use enough to moisten to taste.
Even better the next day.

title: eden island chicken
directions: Mix cream of chicken, sour cream and cream cheese to make sauce.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Layer dish with dry beef.
Put chicken on top of beef.
Cover with the sauce you made.
Cover with foil, but don't seal.
Cook 2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil and brown slightly.

title: 20 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in a large warm mixing bowl. Add sugar, salt and unbeaten egg. Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Beat and add shortening. Fill well-greased muffin pans 1/3 full.
Let rise in warm place until level with pan or about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° or 400° for 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Beat egg; add remaining ingredients in order listed and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Grease heated griddle, if necessary.
To test griddle, sprinkle with a few drops of water. If bubbles skitter around, heat is just right.
Pour batter from tip of large spoon from pitcher onto hot griddle.
Turn pancakes as soon as they are puffed and edges begin to dry slightly.
Bake other side until golden brown.
Makes 10 4-inch pancakes.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water; mix well. Spread half of batter into greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Mix sugar, pecan pieces and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of sugar mixture over batter. Pour remaining batter into pan, top with sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in bowl.
Spread bean dip in bottom of pie plate.
Top with sour cream mixture. Layer peppers, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Then top with grated cheese.
Serve chilled with taco chips.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Combine both sugars and sour cream in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring to 238° on candy thermometer or until a little cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Separate with a fork; let dry.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: squash soup
directions: Melt margarine; add vegetables.
Saute over medium heat until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook a few minutes on low.
Add broth and heat thoroughly.
Add milk and cheese.
Then season with salt and pepper.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine in heavy saucepan the first 2 ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted.
Keep warm. Combine in a large bowl the remaining ingredients except chocolate pieces. By hand, stir until dough holds together. Press half the dough into pan.
Reserve remaining dough for topping. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked crust. Spread caramel mixture over all.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: coffee can bread
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand in warm place until mixture is bubbly, about 16 minutes.
Stir in remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, milk, salt and oil.
With beater on low, beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, beating very well after each addition.
Beat in last cup with a heavy spoon.
Add flour until dough is very heavy and stiff, but too sticky to knead.
Place dough in a well-buttered 2-pound coffee can, or two 1-pound cans, with well-greased plastic lid.

title: cranberry pie
directions: In a pie shell, add cranberries and sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs, flour, sugar and margarine.
Pour over top of cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Parboil cauliflower in water with lemon juice for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine in saucepan: butter, flour, milk and soup.
Cook until thickened.
In baking dish, lay in layers:
cauliflower, cheese slices and chopped green pepper.
Pour creamed sauce over all.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix together butter, syrup and sugar in pan over medium heat until it boils.
Boil for 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add peanuts.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon in heavy pan.
Add apples and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook slowly 10 minutes or until tender.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add pineapple chunks and cheese, then place in one layer in a baking dish. Top pineapple mixture with crumbled crackers. Pour butter on the top layer of crackers. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: glo's key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in two graham cracker crusts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with lime and refrigerate.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into a ball; garnish by rolling in pecans and 1/2 of bacon.
Be creative and design or decorate with olives and pimentos.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll in chopped nuts. Chill before serving.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine the egg, milk and fat. Add gradually to the dry ingredients.
Stir only until batter is smooth.
Fold in apples.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a hot, greased griddle.
Cook slowly until the surface is covered with bubbles. Turn and cook until the bottom is well browned.
(Note:
Make pancakes thin and roll them up before placing in a warm oven.)

title: chile peanuts(yield 6 cups)
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly and toss with warm peanuts.

title: hot sausage hors d'oeuvre
directions: Cook sausage under broiler or charcoal (may be charcoaled ahead and frozen).
Cut into bite size pieces; heat in Ragu sauce and serve from warmer to keep hot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place raw chicken, rice and melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Wash, brush off and cut up root vegetables and onion.
Saute onions 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in root vegetables and cook 5 minutes; add basil or oregano and saute 2 minutes more.
Combine sesame butter, soy sauce and water in a small bowl, blending well.
Put vegetables into an oiled 2-quart oven dish and cover with sauce.
Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into 9x13 baking dish.
Bake for 5 minutes at 375 degrees.
Brown sausage; drain, pour over crust, layer, hash browns and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, jello and flour until well blended.
Add oil, water, eggs and half of strawberries.
Beat on high speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix together.
Chill dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cherry jewels
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add egg yolk, lemon rind, lemon juice, orange juice and vanilla. Beat well.
Gradually blend in flour; chill.
Roll dough into 1-inch diameter balls; roll in nuts and place on buttered baking sheet.
Press cherry half in center.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Add other ingredients, cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and margarine and place in greased baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake for about 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
In a large bowl, combine milk, sugar, Egg Beaters, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread cubes and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish into a pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings. Preparation time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Add apples.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put butter and sugar in top of double boiler. Add 1 cup milk. Heat over boiling water until milk is scalded.
Mix the flour and salt. Stir in 1/2 cup milk, then stir this mixture into the double boiler and continue to stir until this mixture thickens. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Beat the egg yolks slightly. Stir in a little of the hot mixture, then pour in double
boiler and cook 1
minute. Cool slightly.
