Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from 2 egg whites. Brown in oven at 350°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and cocoa. Stir well, then add eggs. Stir. DO NOT BEAT. Add milk and vanilla. Pour in pie crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Then reduce to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: weight watchers delight
directions: Dip bananas, apples and pears in lemon juice.
Drain.
Combine with orange sections in glass bowl.
Chill for 1 hour.
Fold in coconut and yogurt.

title: carob brownies
directions: Cream together first six ingredients.
Add remaining five ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into sprayed 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: molded french cream
directions: Combine sour cream and whipping cream in a medium saucepan. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Cook over low heat until warm. In a small bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add to cream mixture and remove from heat. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add cream mixture and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Pour into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold; chill until firm. Unmold and garnish with additional whipped cream, if desired.

title: grandma's persimmon pudding
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and sherry.
Place over heat and let get hot while stirring.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve.
Get with ham or turkey dinner.

title: carmel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough and break in pieces, put in greased 9x13 pan. Melt together, butter, sugar vanilla pudding, milk and cinnamon. Pour over dough and sit in fridge overnight covered with foil. Bake 25 - 30 min. at 350 degrees or until bread is done.

title: easy seafood salad
directions: Mix well.
Add salad dressing, just enough to make it moist.

title: banana delight
directions: Slice bananas lengthwise through peeling of banana.
Place chocolate chips and marshmallows in slit.
Place on plate and microwave 10 to 15 seconds.

title: quick chuck roast
directions: Place roast in the center of a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in
a roasting pan.
Brush meat with the A.1. sauce.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Spread with the soup. Wrap loosely in foil and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: peter cottontails
directions: Mix 2 cups coconut, apricots and milk.
Chill several hours. Form into small balls and roll in remaining coconut.
Store in cool place or fridge.

title: easy egg brunch
directions: Beat eggs with salt and milk; scramble in butter.
Cook until moist.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with bacon; spread sour cream over.
Top with grated cheese.
This can be refrigerated overnight, brought to room temperature and cooked at 300° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in melted butter and flavoring, mix well.
Add nuts.
Shape into little balls and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large kettle, add enough water to chicken to cover.
Add parsley sprigs, celery, carrot, onion, the 2 teaspoons salt, the pepper and bay leaf.
Cover; bring to boiling and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Sift flour, baking powder and the 1/2 teaspoon salt. Combine milk and oil; add with snipped parsley to dry ingredients. Stir just to moisten.
Drop from tablespoon directly onto chicken in boiling stock.
Cover tightly; return to boiling.
Reduce heat (don't lift cover).
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove dumplings and chicken to hot platter; keep hot.

title: potato filling
directions: Combine butter, onion, celery and seasonings in saucepan and cook until butter is browned and vegetables are tender.
Add bread cubes and mix well.
Using your favorite recipe for mashed potatoes, add 2 cups to filling mixture.
Add enough milk to make a moist mixture.
Place in casserole dish, dotting with butter. Bake at 350° until browned and puffy.

title: bacon wrap - arounds(for microwave)
directions: Wrap 1/3 piece of bacon around a pineapple chunk and secure with a toothpick.
Microwave on High approximately 1 minute per 3 appetizers.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter; mix well.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan (bottom and sides).
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 20 minutes; cool.
Mix slightly cooled Hershey bars with Cool Whip.
Spoon into cooled crust.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Store in freezer.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to margarine mixture.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves.
Drop small pieces of remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares. Yields 36 bars.

title: rum creamer(individual portion)
directions: *Of your liking (example:
butter rum, Irish cream, Amaretto, etc.).

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package says. Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
In small bowl, beat softened cream cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool; glaze, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in bacon fat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add rice and cover with water. Boil 1 minute, while stirring. Cover and cook until rice is fluffy and dry, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy mocha fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square baking pan with foil.
Combine sugar, milk, marshmallow, butter, coffee liqueur and instant coffee in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread fudge into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove fudge from pan and discard foil.
Yields 2 1/2 pounds, 16 pieces.

title: scallops and fettucini in wine sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Saute shallots and scallops. Scallops are done when they first become opaque throughout (do not overcook).
Remove the scallops and shallots and cover to keep them warm.
Stir flour into the juices left in the saucepan until all lumps have dissolved; add wine and cream.
Continue stirring and cook over medium heat until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cheeses.
When almost completely melted, add the scallops, shallots and chives.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Cream the cheese with mixer.
Add milk, baking powder, vanilla and sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in fruit. Sprinkle with pecans. Freeze until firm.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add milk; stir with fork until soft dough is formed.
Place dough on lightly floured board and knead 20 times.
Pat or roll lightly until dough is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut marshmallows and melt in milk on very low heat; cool thoroughly.
Fold in whipping cream and drained strawberries. Pour into vanilla wafer crumb crust.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Cut in wedges and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain and rinse black-eyed peas.
Combine all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: milky way brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup canned milk and 3/4 cup melted margarine together.
Put 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt caramels and 1/3 cup canned milk in microwave or double boiler.
Add caramel mixture over cooked cake.
Then add nuts on top of caramel and then add chocolate chips.
Add (pat) the other 1/2 of cake mixture (this can be hard to spread).
Bake for 15 more minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together, flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: christina's kielbasa dinner
directions: Prepare fettuccine, drain; melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, then vegetables; cook until tender, set aside.
Brown kielbasa and drain.
Combine kielbasa, vegetables and cream; simmer.
Add cheese, parsley, garlic and seasoning salt.
Combine with fettuccine.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
If it appears too thick, add a little more olive oil.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs, 1 cup butter and vanilla.
Spread over crumbs.
Spread on pineapple.
Layer banana slices on top.
Layer strawberries on top of bananas.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane. Precook green peppers in 1 cup boiling, salted water for about 5 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle salt inside peppers.
Brown meat and onions in hot fat; add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce and add salt to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add cheese.

title: saffron curried rice
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Stir in curry powder, saffron and rice.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat margarine and water to rapid boil; stir in flour vigorously over low heat.
Mix until it forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; beat in eggs until smooth.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and golden brown. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops, remove any dough and fill with pudding and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: creamy turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saut onion and celery in margarine. Add broth, cream cheese and soup. Stir over low heat until melted. Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan. Pour into 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, boiling water and salt and let stand until cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Add eggs and flour and mix/knead thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Shape and let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 3 cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before icing.

title: banana nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: crab omelet(egg fu yung)
directions: Break eggs into a large bowl.
Add crab meat, soy sauce, salt, pepper and cornstarch.
Mix all ingredients well.
Heat wok.
Add 2 tablespoons oil.
Stir-fry bamboo shoots and water chestnuts for 30 seconds.
Add onion and celery for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from wok and put aside to cool.
Mix eggs.
Add crabmeat mixture to vegetables.
Mix well.
Reheat wok and add 2 tablespoons oil of mixture (2 tablespoons each).
Add oil if necessary.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Add 1/4 cup chocolate syrup to remaining batter and mix.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle sifted powdered sugar on top.

title: popover pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, milk and eggs.
Batter will be lumpy.
Put butter into 12-inch round frypan.
Place pan in oven and allow to become very hot.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until the pancake is puffed and golden brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and lemon juice.

title: golden pear soup
directions: Steps 1 through 4 can be done ahead of time and the puree can be refrigerated for a day or two before the finishing touches are added and the soup is heated and served. pieces.
Place in a large saucepan with water, cinnamon stick and salt. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until tender (about 15 minutes). Remove the cover and let it simmer an additional 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove and discard the cinnamon stick. Set aside. over medium heat, stirring frequently. Add 1/4 cup wine.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes more over medium heat. puree the yams in their water together with the pears au jus until smooth. (You may have to do this in several batches.)
Transfer to a heavy kettle or Dutch oven. Sprinkle in the white pepper.
Heat very gently just before serving.
(Don't cook it or let it boil.)

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Stir cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth. Set aside. Brown chicken in 2 tbsp. oil. Set aside.

title: five pound candy
directions: Cook slowly until soft-ball stage and set off. Add vanilla. When lukewarm, add pecans. Beat until stiff like. Pour into greased pan. Can halve the recipe.

title: blondies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts and chocolate, in a large mixer bowl. Stir in half of the nuts and chocolate morsels. Coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with soft-type margarine.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining nuts and chocolate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut in bars.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Form into balls and roll in flour. Brown. Cover with beef broth or bouillon. Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour. Gravy can be made from broth in pan. Serves 6-8 people.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Lay bread
slices on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan; sprinkle
cheese
on top.
Sprinkle sausage on top;
mix eggs, milk,
mustard, salt and pepper, pour on top.
Soak overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly and firm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Dip your favorite vegetables!

title: favorite oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour boiling water over baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Add flour; mix.
Add oatmeal; mix.
Add chocolate chips and nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes (soft cookie) to 10 minutes (hard cookie).

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, juice, ginger, garlic and sugar to form the marinade.
Wash chicken pieces and add to bowl.
Marinate chicken for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once or twice.*
Remove chicken from marinade.
Arrange in a baking pan. Pour marinade over chicken.

title: easy and delicious chicken
directions: Mix together ingredients. Coat chicken with mixture. Add any additional mixture to baking dish.

title: emerald salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in the hot water and add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Boil and simmer hamburger meat, onion and 1 cup water.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: turtles
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Press half of batter into 9 x 13 pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple in its juice and stir in jello.
Cool. Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Will fill large flat casserole.

title: texas hush puppies
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal.
Chill mixture for 1 hour. Heat 2 tablespoons shortening in a heavy skillet.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: you always ask for seconds
directions: Line 9 x 11-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Spread, while warm, over graham crackers.
Cover with
a large layer of graham crackers.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Spread this mixture on top.

title: snow ghost cocoa cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into shell.
Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the night before.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve water and Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until completely congealed.

title: spinach balls
directions: Precook and drain spinach well.
I remove water by squeezing with my hands.
Mix everything and chill well.
Roll into walnut size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Then put in plastic bags.
Bake as many as you need at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: iced apple tea
directions: Place tea bags in a pitcher; cover with boiling water.
Steep for 5 minutes.
Squeeze tea bags and discard.
Stir in honey until dissolved.
Stir in apple juice.
Chill or add ice cubes to glasses.
Pour into tall glass; add lemon slice and mint spring. Very refreshing!

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.
My gang loves this!

title: thyme roasted potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes, oil, salt and pepper until potatoes are coated. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Toss in thyme leaves.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: country ham biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour with pastry cutter until crumbly. Add buttermilk, sour cream and ham. Stir until moistened. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead several times. Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Grease bundt pan well.
Line bottom with pecan pieces.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Melt oleo, add brown sugar and cinnamon and more pecans.
Pour over rolls.
Cover and let set overnight on counter to raise.
Bake 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and the whole orange.
Cook in the 2 cups water until tender.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Let cool until partially set.
Stir in celery and nuts.
This is even better if made a day ahead.

title: daily bread
directions: Mix yeast with liquid which is warm (105° to 115°).
Add remaining ingredients, except flour.
Mix well.
Let sit a few minutes for yeast to "proof" (it will begin to bubble).
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
At some point, you will need to put dough on a board which is generously floured.
Continue adding flour until dough can be easily worked.
(It is hard to predetermine the amount of flour needed as moisture contents of flours vary.) You'll develop a "feel" for this.
Shape rolls or loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350°, 8 to 10 minutes for rolls or 20 to 30 minutes for loaves.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together by hand all ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Cook on cookie sheet at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix the wet and dry ingredients together, then spread in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake a 325 for 30 minutes.

title: pork sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes. Serve hot.

title: happy time punch
directions: Combine juice and water in separate bowl.
Place sherbet and ice cream in punch bowl.
Break into small pieces with large spoon.
Add juices and stir until blended.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Put sliced fruit in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and add 1/2 of the sugar.
Mix well.
Mix flour, rest of sugar, baking powder and salt.
Drop egg in and stir until crumbly.
Pat mixture down on top of fruit.
Pour melted butter over all and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh corn cakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl beat egg yolks, blend in milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until mixed (batter may be slightly lumpy).
Stir in onions, corn, red peppers and green chilies; set aside.
In a small bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gently fold in batter.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto slightly greased griddle; brown on both sides.
Yields 20 pancakes.

title: special cookie bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn flake crumbs, butter and sugar. Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chips, nuts and coconut. Drizzle with milk. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool on wire rack before cutting. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thin in bowl.
Slice onions diagonally as thin as possible and add to cucumbers.
Combine vinegar, sugar, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Whisk with fork until well blended.
Pour over onions and cucumbers.
Turn with spatula to cover all pieces. Marinate 1 hour or more.
Lift cucumbers from marinade.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown chicken breasts in frypan.
While cooking, season to taste with salt, pepper, parsley and garlic powder.
Cook for approximately 15 minutes.
Place chicken in casserole dish and spread salsa over breasts.

title: salsa potato skins
directions: To Make Ahead: Microwave the potatoes 1 day ahead; scoop out the pulp. Wrap the skins in plastic wrap and refrigerate. Butter and bake before serving.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add Cheez Whiz and melt with butter.
Cook onion and broccoli until tender (drain).
Mix Minute rice, mushroom soup and milk.
Pour all together and stir.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until rice is tender.

title: twice-baked potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes.
Place half in a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of salt, pepper, and bacon.
Top with half of the sour cream and mozarella and cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with onions.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Chop or
grind onions, peppers and pimentos.
Drain off liquid.
Blend in all other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: settler's beans
directions: Brown beef, green pepper and onion. Drain.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly, at least 45 minutes.

title: maraschino cherry cake
directions: Mix nuts and cherries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Combine cake flour, baking powder, salt, cherry juice and milk (which has been mixed together) and fold in the egg whites.
Bake 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes, rinse and boil with jackets on. After potatoes have cooled, peel and cut in 1/4 inch slices. Cook bacon and onion in hot pan until bacon is crisp and onion is transparent. Add vinegar, stock, and seasonings. Stir and let come to boil. Stir in egg yolk; remove from heat and pour over potatoes. Serves 2 - 4.

title: cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into cup and add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat to boil.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add pineapple, milk and mayonnaise.
Stir to cool then add cheese and refrigerate.

title: cabbage roll-ups
directions: Soak cabbage leaves in salt water for 10 minutes.
Mix hamburger, sausage, rice, catsup, crackers, Worcestershire sauce, eggs and celery salt.
Shape into balls and place in cabbage leaves.
Roll up.
Put layer of sauerkraut into baking dish. Cover with shredded cabbage.
Place cabbage roll-ups on top of this.
Cover with a small can of tomato sauce.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Season flour to taste.
Wash wings; dredge in flour as if you're frying chicken.
Fry in deep fryer until crispy and done. While chicken is cooking, mix remaining ingredients together in large bowl.
Pull chicken from deep fryer; strain excess grease. Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt and dip in sauce.
Let marinate for 10 minutes, then strain excess sauce.
You're ready to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: e z butter cookies
directions: Mix butter until very, very soft.
Add sugar and beat until well blended.
Add flour slowly until well blended.
Press evenly onto two cookie sheets.
When still warm, cut into sticks.
You can press chopped nuts or sesame seed onto top before baking. Bake at 350° until very light brown.
Watch them as they brown very quickly.

title: tony's macaronies
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions until tender. Drain.
Rinse the dry cottage cheese thoroughly.
Saute onions in butter.
Add cottage cheese and macaroni and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: hot dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in shallow baking dish. Saut 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped pecans in 2 tablespoons butter. Spread on top. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sherry poppy seed cake
directions: Combine and mix 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, depending on size of pan.
Not recommended for eating just before drug testing!

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs, oil, cheese, onion and squash.
Add Bisquick until well coated.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch square pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: noels
directions: Cream together the margarine and powdered sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Partially cool; roll balls in more powdered sugar.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook, debone and cut up chicken.
Put Doritos in 2 baking dishes.
Pour 3/4 cup chicken broth over chips.
Salt with dash of garlic salt.
Layer chicken over chips.
Top with onions and peppers.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Heat soup and chili powder with 1 1/2 cups broth.
Pour over casserole.
Top with Ro-Tel and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese melts.

title: potatoes ryan
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cool and then spoon out centers.
Crumble into big chunks.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Pour cream over and allow to sit 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top, then bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg yolks, vanilla and salt. Beat well, then gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Make 3/4-inch balls.
Dip in egg whites; roll in walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press center with thumb.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes at 350°.
When cool, fill with colored icing or jelly.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Add butter and egg to cake mix.
Mix with fork.
It will be doughy.
Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: water whipped baked pastry shell
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in deep mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add flour and salt; beat on low speed until dry mixture is moistened. Divide dough in half; shape into balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours.
Remove one dough portion at a time.
Place between 12-inch long pieces of wax paper.
Roll into a 12-inch circle; peel away wax paper and place in a 9-inch pie plate and flute edges.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Repeat procedure with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Yield: two 9-inch pie shells.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside. Mix sugar and softened butter together.
Add eggs one at time. Mix raw apples in and coat evenly.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put
in
x 13-inch pan. Beat next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Bake
for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Top with pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add oil and sweetener.
Mix until light.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Fresh apples may be used instead of bananas.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add onion salt and garlic salt to taste.
Add parsley flakes (optional).
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Warm milk.
Add dry ingredients and egg yolks.
Cook until thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: chinese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, then add softened butter.
Cream butter, sugar and add the beaten eggs.
Add nuts and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: millie's baked beans
directions: Saute first 2 ingredients together in small amount of butter. Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pan or very large baking casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brickle crunch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour and soda, then brickle and nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° just until delicately browned.
Watch closely, so they don't get too crisp.

title: pork tenderloin goulash
directions: Cut pork in cubes about 1-inch in size.
Roll in flour and brown in small amount of cooking oil.
In bowl, stir together the soup, 1 can water, dry soup mix and undrained mushrooms.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted margarine, cocoa and salt.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Combine all with milk, adding to desired consistency. Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake.

title: roasted veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut all vegetables into 1/2-inch chunks.
Toss potatoes, yams and squash with 2 tablespoons olive oil so all sides are coated.
Spread vegetables in a single layer in 2 shallow baking pans and put in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Toss onions and peppers with remaining oil.
Add to pan in oven; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast until vegetables are browned and begin to dehydrate, about another 20 minutes.
Delicious hot or cold.
May add 1 tablespoon curry powder.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter in pan.
Bring to boil and add flour all at once.
Stir until the paste comes away from the sides of the pan.
When cold, add the unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Chill in icebox.
Drop by tablespoon on oiled paper (12 puffs).
Bake 30 minutes in hot oven.
When cold fill with whipped cream or thick custard when time to serve.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple with juice to a boil.
Add dry jello and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat to cool.
When cooled, add buttermilk and then nuts.
Add Cool Whip last.
Stir until mixed well.
Refrigerate.

title: butter pecan cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In a large bowl, blend 2 cups flour, brown
sugar
and	margarine
until
crumbly.
Stir in pecans. Press
crumb mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°	for 15	minutes, or until light golden brown.
In small bowl,
beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Blend in 2 tablespoons flour
and	eggs.
Pour filling over baked crust. Sprinkle butterscotch
chips on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 15
to 20	minutes, or until firm to touch.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.	Cut into bars when cool.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute
rice and onion in butter in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Melt Crisco.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and beginning to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard and cheese.
Arrange layers of potatoes, wieners and cheese sauce in 2-quart casserole which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Top with cheese sauce.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve hot.

title: straw hay
directions: Boil linguini in salted water; drain.
Add butter, ham, peas and mushrooms.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks and cream with fork until foamy.
Slowly add cream mix to linguini.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir gently over medium heat until thickened.
Add remainder Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: pink fruit punch
directions: Put all ingredients into punch bowl except ginger ale.
Make sure to stir mixture until sugar is dissolved.
Chill mixture until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating; set pan aside.
In a small mixing bowl combine 3/4 cup flour and 3 tablespoons granulated sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Pat mixture onto the bottom of the prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add all of the ingredients together. Grease a 1-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until inserted knife comes out dry or clean.

title: pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers (1/4-inch thick) into jar (1 gallon).
Fill jar with vinegar and spices; let stay for 60 days.
Drain off vinegar and add dry sugar until jar is full of syrup, made from the sugar.

title: frosted lime cheese salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin; stir until dissolved. Refrigerate, stirring occasionally until consistency of egg white. Add pineapple, cottage cheese, celery, pimento and walnuts.
Pour into 2-inch deep flat pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: chess pies
directions: Beat eggs with table knife; add butter, sugar, flour and nuts. Pour in shells (8 to package at Woodman's).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: apple-cheese
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add cheese; beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Put apples in buttered casserole and cover with mixture. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
(Watch carefully, cheese cooks fast.)
Serve with meal; tastes good enough for dessert!

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add syrup; fold in eggs.
add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: summer squash pie(yellow)
directions: Wash and cut off both ends, grate entire squash, rind included and mix with the above mixture.
Put into two 9-inch pie tins. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: down east apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8-inch greased pan.
Blend rest of ingredients until crumbly, then spread over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mash up the ingredients in a bowl and roll into 1-inch (or a little smaller) balls.
Bake at 375° until crispy (about 15 minutes).
Serve with Dijon mustard for dipping.
Makes 30 to 40.

title: ham delites
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together. Split dinner rolls. Spread tops and bottoms with mixture. Add ham and cheese to bottom of dinner roll. Cover with top bread. Then cover in foil and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: ham and cheese wrapped sausage
directions: Place ribs in a large Dutch oven or kettle with enough water to cover. Add salt, lemon and onion and cook 45 to 60 minutes. Drain ribs thoroughly, discarding lemon and onion slices. Brush ribs well with sauce and place over slow coals. Turn every 10 minutes; brush frequently with sauce. Cook from 35 to 45 minutes or until done and well coated with sauce. Makes 8 servings.

title: dipping mustard sauce for ribs
directions: Add water to mustard; mix to blend well.
Stir in oil and salt.
Makes 2/3 cup sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix well until blended.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: bob's chili
directions: Put chopped tomatoes in crock-pot; add beans and chili mix. Brown ground chuck and drain; put in crock-pot.
Brown onion and celery in butter; add to mixture.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours at 150°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg in large mixing bowl.
Add milk and oil, blending well.
Add dry ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups (12) to 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from muffin pan immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper, margarine, cracker crumbs, 1/2 of cheese, milk and egg; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pink stuff(salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill!!

title: reunion squares
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk.
Mix cake with remaining milk, butter, and walnuts.
In a buttered and floured 9 x 13 inch pan, spread half of the cake mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 6 minutes.
While hot, add chocolate chips on top. Spread caramel mixture over that, and then remaining cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: steak sylvester
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Brown quickly in oil.
Drain oil, leaving brown in bottom of skillet.
Brown the cut onion tops.
Pour some water over onions and return steak to skillet.
Add Worcestershire and soy sauce to taste.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
This is a thin dark gravy.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
When cake is done, let cool. Take strawberries and drain juice from them.
Poke holes in cake and pour juice over it.
Frost cake with frosting.
Take strawberries and put all over top of cake.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: fettuccine with fresh tomatoes and basil
directions: In large pan of boiling salted water, cook fettuccine al dente; drain.
In heavy skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, garlic, basil and sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Add to tomato mixture with cheese; toss to mix.

title: mama clayton's divinity candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients
over	medium	heat
until
it forms a hard ball when tested
in
cold
water.
Beat
2	egg whites until stiff.
Then	pour
syrup mixture slowly over egg whites. Beat until mixture begins
to lose its gloss and soft peaks form. Spoon drops onto wax paper and let cool.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip together. Pour into graham cracker crust; refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
This can be portioned out as desired.
Three tablespoons of mix makes 1 cup when added to milk or water.

title: chicken breast dijon
directions: Preheat skill and oil.
Pound breast until about 1 1/2 times original size.
Coat liberally with mustard, then dredge in bread crumbs.
Saute on both sides until just firm and starting to brown, 3 minutes per side.
Cover and steam in natural juices for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: english chutney(this is a very old family recipe.)
directions: Chop all ingredients in fine dice.
Cook slowly for 3 hours; pack and seal.
Modern day hint, grind cinnamon sticks in mini coffee grinder.
My mama placed them in double layers of cheesecloth and smashed them with a hammer!
This is very good served along side baked ham, roast beef, roast chicken and other meats.

title: pay day bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and pour over Chex.
Mix in peanuts.
Mix well. Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, chopped pimentos, peas and soup. Top with crushed crackers and cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and raisins.
Stir in cream with fork until moistened.
Turn dough into floured surface; knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll or press to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, place on baking tin (lightly greased) and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground meat and chopped onion in a large skillet or Dutch oven.

title: crab soup
directions: Combine and heat first 4 ingredients. Add crab. Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup sherry.
Paprika and parsley may be added before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: working girl's supper casserole
directions: Put raw ground meat in bottom of glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay Tater Tots all over top of meat.
Mix soups and water together; pour over meat and Tater Tots.
Put in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with salad.

title: no-bake chocolate caramel bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Combine chocolate chips and shortening in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir vigorously.
If necessary, microwave on High an additional 30 seconds at a time, stirring vigorously after each heating, just until chips are melted.
Pour cereal into melted chip mixture.
Stir until thoroughly coated.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Drizzle 1 1/2 cubes butter over cake mix, followed by nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: corn and pepper chowder
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and red pepper in oil until tender. Stir in flour and cumin until blended. Gradually stir in water. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat. Add the potatoes, bouillon, salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add corn and milk. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer or until heated through. Garnish with cilantro. Yield: 6 servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage until cooked; drain liquid off.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Trim crust from bread if desired.
Place 6 slices bread, butter side up, into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 sausage and cheese over bread.
Place remaining 6 slices of bread on top and remainder sausage, then cheese.
Pour egg mixture on top and press down with spatula until milk comes to top of casserole. Refrigerate if desired overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 45 minutes before you cook.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine Bisquick with cheddar cheese, milk, melted butter and garlic powder.
Mix until well combined. Drop by 1/4 cup portions of dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well mixed.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and peanut butter well.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill well before serving.
Suitable for freezing.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add shortening and sugar, then eggs. Add flour and salt.
Cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before making them out in rolls.
After making, let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in casserole dish in microwave according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, Cheez Whiz and onions.
Heat.
Add rice.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: grandma's potatoes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Cut flour, baking powder and salt into the shortening.
Add milk sparingly and stir until the dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn dough on floured surface, roll to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut dough with biscuit cutter, set on cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cereal, butter and sugar.
Pat mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato cakes
directions: Put the pan drippings (or Crisco) in a large frying pan.
Put on low heat while you prepare the potato pancakes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.

title: beef 'n cheese filling(for mexican pizza)
directions: In a large frying pan, lightly brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer one minute.
Spoon over crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until filling is hot and bubbly.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and beans.
Cook for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Cream shortening, salt and lemon extract.
Add sugar gradually and the eggs, one at a time. Beat until mixture looks like whipped cream.
Alternately add the dry ingredients, which have been sifted together with milk.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Braise onion in margarine.
Beat eggs slightly and combine all ingredients well.
Place in oiled 8 x 8-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until set.
Serve with brown gravy.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut milk cake
directions: Add cake mix to bowl.
Add oil, eggs, pudding mix and thawed coconut milk.
Blend.
Mix for 2 minutes with mixer.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cake may be eaten plain or with a frosting of your choice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook the squash in salted water until just tender (do not overcook).
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper to tomatoes and cook until thickened.
Place squash in casserole, add tomato mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Melt oleo, applesauce and brown sugar. In a 2-quart casserole, drain and cut in bite-size pieces the pears, peaches and bananas. Pour sauce over all and stir. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Last 30 minutes, add chopped nuts, stirred in well.

title: emmy's pasta salad
directions: Cut vegetables fine.
Mix with pasta.
Add 1 bottle McCormick Salad Supreme and 1 (12 ounce) bottle Italian dressing.
Mix well.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Combine ingredients until well blended.
Bake in two 9 inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely, then split layers into four layers.

title: clara's apple dessert
directions: Chop up apples and put in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar until well covered, but apples can still be seen.
Flour lightly over apples.
Take the cake mix (don't add anything to it) and spread over apples.
Slice up a stick of butter and cover cake mix almost completely.
Cook at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes or until cake mix if light brown.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Saute onion.
Cover bottom of crust with cheese and ham.
Add onion.
Combine eggs, cream, milk and flour with a pinch of nutmeg, a few grains of cayenne and black pepper.
Stop here if preparing ahead. Immediately before cooking, pour cream mixture over the ham and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and at 325° for 30 minutes. If doing ahead, let shell and custard mixture stand at room temperature before baking.
This may be fully prepared and baked for freezing.

title: peach tapioca dessert
directions: Bring 3 cups
water to boiling point.
Soak tapioca in other cup of water while water comes to boil, stirring occasionally. Add tapioca to water and
bring to boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add sugar, salt
and
orange
juice.
Just before serving, add 1 quart frozen peaches and 1 1/2 cups sliced bananas.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach with soup; spread 1/2 mixture in flat baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup both cheeses.
Cover with remaining spinach, then sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peasant pizza
directions: Thaw dough and cut each loaf in half to make 4 pieces.
Let rise about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until double.
Mix spices in oil. Brush on dough.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Remove, slightly flatten with a fork.
Brush with extra oil and spices.
Place sliced tomatoes and cheese on each pizza.
Return to oven about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: to can steak
directions: Dissolve salt and sugar
in water.
Bring to boil.
Add about 1 cup to a quart
jar
and
put
steaks
in.
Enough for about 16 quarts.
Cold pack
for
1/2 hours or can pressure can at 10 pound pressure for 45 minutes.

title: nanny's cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour batter into 4 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Let cool completely on wire racks.
(Layers are very tender and fragile, so handle them carefully.)

title: fried okra(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cut tops off the okra and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix egg with 2 tablespoons water and toss with okra.
Add cornmeal and salt and pepper.
Mix well so all pieces are coated.
Pan-fry over medium heat.
Shake so pieces separate and brown evenly on both sides.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Combine cheese and powdered sugar and put in bottom of shell. Fold in large tub of whipped topping mixed with 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans.
Top with 1 carton frozen raspberries thickened with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Place pea beans in slow cooker. Add water to 1 inch above beans; cover. Turn heat to High and cook for 3 hours. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover. Cook on Low 10 to 14 hours or until beans are tender.

title: "sunny jim" casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch casserole. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: strawberries and cream shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, rind (if desired) and salt; cut in shortening until crumbly.
In medium bowl, combine milk, egg and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spread into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: fast and easy
directions: Bring medium saucepan of water (lightly salted) to boil.
Add noodles and cook for (8) eight minutes.
Drain water off noodles. Add margarine.
Stir well.
then add can of soup.
Stir again. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A can of corn can be substituted if you do not have 4 different beans. You can also put chopped ham or hot dogs in it.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Chill well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: taco baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until soft when pierced with a fork.
Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is browned; drain well.
Add seasoning mix and water; reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Split tops of potatoes lengthwise and fluff pulp with a fork.
Spoon topping over potatoes.
Top each with 1 tablespoon sour cream.

title: shredded apple pie
directions: Stir ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot butter on top.
Cook about 50 minutes at 400°.

title: marinade for grilled steaks or london broil
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the beef; pour over the meat in a covered container.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Grill the meat to your own taste for medium to medium-rare or well done, using the remainder of the marinade for a basting sauce.

title: baked alaska
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold in sugar.
Place layer cake bottom on an ovenproof plate.
Spread jam evenly over bottom.
Cover with ice cream.
Immediately spread meringue evenly over top.
Meringue should cover ice cream completely.
Bake at 350° for a couple of minutes until meringue has a light brown color.
Serve immediately.

title: blueberry oat muffins
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans filling 3/4 full. Bake at 400° 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Freeze 7-Up in Bundt pan to put in punch bowl to float.

title: cream christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Gradually add sugar; mix well.
Add milk and flavoring; mix well.
Fold Cool Whip into eggnog.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Add quart eggnog (optional).
Cut ice cream in half.
Place in punch bowl.
Pour eggnog mixture over ice cream and serve.
Yields 24 to 30 cups.

title: pineapple-cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl except crumbs.
Roll this mixture in the graham cracker crumbs.
Place in refrigerator and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: bronzed cajun cream pheasant breast
directions: Remove skin from breast.
Rub breast with cajun seasoning on both sides.
Sprinkle with olive oil and place in plastic bag for at least one hour.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix jello dry with cottage cheese.
Drain juice from fruit and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.
Serves 10.

title: old-fashioned cream bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, combine cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add diced onion, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Layer hamburger mixture, taco shells and cheese until mixture is used up, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 400° covered for 20 minutes.
Serve with chopped tomato, onion, lettuce and cheese on top.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with dressing. Sprinkle with fresh garlic chips.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May place in refrigerator overnight before cooking.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine dates and boiling water.
Mix and let cool.
Mix white sugar, brown sugar, egg and melted oleo.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; combine with sugar mixture and mix well.
Add dates.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan (9 x 9-inch makes cake thicker).
Combine the 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour over batter. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: back forty stew
directions: During hunting season this was a camp favorite.
It is easy to make and takes a couple of hours to simmer.

title: eggs sardou for eight
directions: Saute green onions in butter until tender; stir in spinach and next 6 ingredients. Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated (do not boil). Place 16 artichoke bottoms on baking sheets; bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until heated; keep warm. Spoon 2 tablespoons spinach mixture onto a warm dinner plate; top with 2 artichoke bottoms. Arrange a poached egg on each bottom. Spoon 3 tablespoons Hollandaise Sauce over eggs; sprinkle with paprika.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine
in saucepan over low heat. Add cocoa; stir until blended.	Remove from heat and in bowl, beat eggs
and
sugar
together until thick.
Add vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Beat
well.
Stir in flour until blended. Pour into greased
8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and break up into pieces and cool.

title: pinkito beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and soak overnight.
While beans and ham hocks are boiling, chop onion and garlic (not too fine).
Brown in skillet with vegetable oil, then add chili powder and tomato sauce.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
When beans are half done, add sauce and salt and pepper.
Continue to boil until done.
Cook approximately 3 hours.
Will feed approximately 20 people.

title: chitterlings
directions: Cook chitterlings for 1 hour or until tender.
Drain off water and remove onion.
Prepare iron skillet with margarine.
Cut chitterlings in 2-inch pieces and fry until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite side dishes, such as macaroni and cheese, rice or greens.
Hot sauce is also offered.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in 3-inch squares to serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Don't pare cucumbers.
Slice then add onions and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours and drain. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers.
Heat to a boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: fresh frozen sweet corn
directions: Mix together.
Place in saucepan; cook over medium heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put in separate pan to let it cool.
Put in quart bags.
Freeze.

title: bertha's sweet pickle sticks
directions: Select fresh firm cucumbers about 4 1/2 inches long.
Wash and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over and let stand overnight. Next day, drain.
Pack solidly into clean jars.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour this boiling hot liquid over the cucumbers in the jars.
Place cap on jar, screw on band tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Makes 3 pints.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in top of double boiler.
Add water. Combine beaten egg yolks and lemon juice; beat.
Pour in double boiler.
Cook until thick, then add vinegar and extract.
Cool, then pour into pie shell.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugars, egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine other ingredients.
Add to cream mixture.
Mix well. Place walnut size pieces of dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a glass dipped in water.
Bake in 325° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine all ingredients, shake and let settle for 4 hours. For best results, use these name brands.
Save bubble wands from purchased bottles.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Fix it like it says.
Follow the directions on the package, that is what you do.

title: butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix and butter.
Spread into greased 10x13 pan. Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Spread mixture over cake mix, leave 1/2 inch edge.

title: sangria
directions: Peel and cut up 1 orange.
Cut apple into 1/2-inch squares. Peel and cut up 1/2 of the lemon.
Juice the other orange and 1/2 of lemon.
Mix all the ingredients except the ice into a pitcher. Add ice 1/2 hour before serving.

title: crunchy cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine cereal, 1 cup of brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon; set aside. Mix together baking mix, remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 1/4 cups of milk, eggs and oil until just blended. Pour half of batter into 9 x 13 pan sprayed with cooking spray; sprinkle with half of cereal mixture. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Whisk together powdered sugar, remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and remaining 2 tablespoons milk until well blended. Drizzle over coffee cake. Let stand until set. Makes 24 servings.

title: peanut butter rice krispies squares
directions: Cook sugar and syrup on medium heat and boil until little bubbles form.
Mix peanut butter, Rice Krispies and nuts with the syrup mixture.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt all chips in double boiler and spread on top of squares.

title: company chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast between two sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Use meat mallet or rolling pin. Combine eggs and milk.
Brush side of chicken with milk.
Put a piece of ham and piece of cheese in center of chicken breast. Brush cheese with milk mixture.
Turn ends over cheese and ham. Roll up, beginning with long side.
Secure with toothpicks. Dredge chicken in flour.
Dip in remaining milk mixture.
Coat well with bread crumbs.
Cover
and chill 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm. Pour warm water into large bowl; sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm mixture, egg and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour, mixing well.
Place dough in greased bowl; brush top with margarine.
Cover tightly with waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Refrigerate until doubled in bulk (up to 4 days).
To use, pinch down; cut off amount of dough required to form into favorite shapes.
Cover; let rise in warm, draft free place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: "old black joe" chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda and salt; beat in eggs, oil, milk and hot coffee.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable tortellini
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Use 1/2 can Durkee onions in the mixture.
Pour in a 2.8 liter baking dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 of Durkee onions on top for the last 10 minutes of baking.
Cover while baking.

title: fruit cake fudge
directions: Into an 8-quart or larger bowl, put ingredients.
Put sugar-milk mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Cook over high heat to 230°.
Remove from heat and pour over ingredients in the mixing bowl, stirring until the chocolate is dissolved.
Spoon onto prepared cookie sheet and spread smooth. Cut when firm.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Makes 6 to 7 pounds fudge.

title: breakfast buns
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Spread marmalade over bottom; sprinkle with nuts.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in butter, then in sugar mixture and stand on side in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle any remaining sugar over ring and drizzle with any remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Serve over ice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs; sift together flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: linda's easy pleasing meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce. Shape meat mixture into 2 oval loaves, side by side in 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with remaining 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until center is no longer pink. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper in oil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer slowly until rice is cooked, stirring often, about 45 minutes.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Fry and crumble bacon; slice or shred cabbage and dice onion and apple.
Put all in pot and add one cup water.
Bring to boil and reduce heat to low.
Simmer until done, about 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Freeze if you like.
Serve with Polish sausage.
Heat sausage with cabbage or alone.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add onion and pepper and garlic powder to melted butter in skillet and heat briefly.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes over low heat.
Add rice and crab to tomato mixture; combine well and pour into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soups, broth and Veg-All together and pour over chicken.

title: rye bread pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on a slice of rye bread. Roll bread.
Slice into pinwheels.
Use toothpicks to hold together.
Broil until slightly brown.
Delicious.

title: oven barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle the brisket with the onion, garlic and celery salt. Marinate overnight in liquid smoke.
In the morning, sprinkle the meat with salt and pepper to taste and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in liquid smoke 5 hours in heavy foil at 275° or until meat is tender.
Baste with barbecue sauce and bake a little longer.
Let cool and slice.
Reheat if necessary.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks. Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.

title: bestemore's baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Fry the bacon.
Drain fat and combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° until thoroughly heated (about 1 hour).
Can be heated in crock-pot for 4 hours or longer.
Serves 18 to 20 (great for potlucks and gatherings).

title: party salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and blend well.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Simply mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
Tasty dessert in less than 15 minutes!
No cooking, no chilling required.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and milk mixed with soda. Add oatmeal, flour and floured nuts and raisins. Add cinnamon with vanilla. Add more milk, if necessary.
Drop on greased pans. Bake at 375° for about 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix melted butter and crumbs.
Cover bottom of pan with 1/2 mixture.
Beat Dream Whip, milk and vanilla until stiff.
Add softened cream cheese and blend well.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over crumbs.
Then spread cherry pie filling on top.
Spread remaining Dream Whip mixture; add remaining crumbs on top.
Let stand overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Makes about 60.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: grand marnier cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar approximately 10 minutes (medium).
Add eggs, sour cream, heavy cream, vanilla, lemon juice and Grand Marnier.
Butter 10 x 3-inch cake pan and dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour in batter.
Place pan into larger pan and fill space with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until slightly brown on top.
Allow to cool.
Best when refrigerated 24 hours.

title: southern plantation sweet potatoes
directions: Bake washed potatoes at 450° for 40 minutes.
Cut slice from side of each and hollow out.
Mash the potato; whip with melted butter, salt, pepper and wine.
Re-stuff into potato shells. Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown in oven.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls in cookie pan (15 x 10-inch).
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Add enough flour to make dough easily handled, about 3 1/2 cups.
Roll and cut biscuits.
Place in pan and set in warm place to rise, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake in 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh apples with caramel sauce
directions: Mix cream cheese and caramel sauce.
Serve with apples. (Sprinkle apples with fresh lemon juice or Fruit Fresh to keep them from turning brown.)

title: cheese bake
directions: In 8 x 8 pan; layer Monterrey jack, cheddar cheese and peppers in 3 layers. In a separate bowl mix eggs, flour and milk; pour over layers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quince preserves
directions: Slice quinces and apples.
Add sugar and water.
Add pineapple, if desired.
Boil until tender.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and top with 1 package of crushed Waverly Wafers crackers, mixed with 1 stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: granddaddy's peanut butter balls(candy)
directions: Place
chocolate and wax in double boiler and let melt. Mix margarine,	peanut	butter	and
sugar.
Roll
into small balls. Dip
each
ball into melted mixture and place on waxed paper
to harden.
Round
toothpicks	can be used as dippers. Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: strawberry twinkie dessert
directions: Combine strawberries and glaze in a small bowl. Slice Twinkies in half lengthwise and place in a single layer over bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and spread mixture over Twinkies. Spoon strawberry mixture over cream cheese mixture. Cover and chill.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients, then take 1/2 of the mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (no longer).
Cool real good.

title: instant spiced hot tea
directions: Mix
and
store in airtight container.	Mix 3 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water to serve.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift salt, soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well.
Beat until batter is smooth.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix peaches, syrup, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg in large bowl.
Spread evenly in 9-inch square baking pan.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: hobos
directions: Shape the hamburger into 4 patties and place each patty on a square of aluminum foil.
Place 1 potato and 1 carrot around each patty and spread catsup over patties.
Place 1 onion slice on each patty.
Fold the foil over and seal ends.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple mix in jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool and add the Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Nuts of any kind may be added.
Pour into large container.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend sugar and flour.
Add eggs; mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This makes its own crust.

title: microwave caramel corn #1
directions: Pop corn; put in grocery bag sprayed with Pam.
In large bowl, mix brown sugar, margarine, syrup, salt and vanilla; cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook on High 3 more minutes.
Add baking soda. Pour brown sugar mixture over popcorn in bag and shake.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake and turn bag over.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Place on cookie sheet and cool.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare pizza dough as directed.
Roll out about 1/4 inch thick.
Using a sharp knife or pizza cutter, cut dough into narrow strips 1/2-inch wide.
Then cut into 3-inch sticks.
Dip sticks into melted margarine and roll in mixture of cheese, oregano and garlic salt.
Place on lightly oiled pan about 3/4 inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen sticks.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
While hot, stir in sherbet.
Fold in Cool Whip.
(Add hot mixture gradually to the Cool Whip to avoid lumps.)
Drain and add mandarin oranges.
Chill.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.

title: bavarian casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with bacon.
Drain sauerkraut and put over bacon.
Lay pork chops over kraut.
Peel and slice potatoes over pork chops.
Slice onions and separate into rings. Put on potatoes.
Pour can of tomatoes on top of casserole (do not drain).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at least 2 hours at 350°. (For first hour, you may want to cover with foil.)

title: roger's blazing beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a large baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix onion and parsley in mayonnaise.
Place cucumbers in layers with dressing.
Salt cucumbers lightly.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, water and pudding.
Beat well and chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Layer each ingredient:
pudding, wafers, bananas, pudding; end with wafers.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine the sugar and flour in a bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except the butter and the pastry shells.
Pour in pie shell and dot with butter.
Add the top crust.
Cut slits in top of crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce the temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with wedge of cheese, if desired.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Fry hamburger and drain fat.
Add oregano, salt and pepper and sauce to the hamburger.
In a casserole dish, layer noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. You can also add pepperoni to this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with hot water.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, a little at a time, beat after each addition.
Bake in paper-lined pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Makes 16 portions.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Make jello as directed.
Wait for jello to congeal.
Mix fruit cocktail and Cool Whip together.
Then add jello and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight.

title: quick peanut butter cake
directions: Empty cake mix into a bowl; add water, egg white and peanut butter.
Blend for 4 or 5 minutes or until creamy.
Transfer to 8-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Allow cake to cool, then remove from pan.
You can also use regular cake mix.
Yields 10 servings.
Exchange 1 serving for 1 starch/bread, 1 1/2 fat, if you're watching your diet.
One serving is 125 calories.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Line cooked pie shell with 2 cups blueberries.
Cook remaining berries with sugar, cornstarch, salt, and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat, add butter and allow to cool.
Pour mixture over berries in pie shell and chill until serving time.

title: italian herb mix
directions: Measure equal amounts of the ingredients and mix all together.

title: crunchy bran muffins
directions: Combine
buttermilk and soda;
set aside.
Cream butter and brown
sugar
thoroughly.
Add
egg
and
beat well.
Add buttermilk	and
soda, then molasses and bran and blend.
Stir in flour
and	salt mixture and fold in fruit and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased
muffin tins and bake at 375° for 20 minutes until well done.

title: mexican layered dessert tortilla(postre de tortilla)
directions: Brush butter
on
both sides of each tortilla.	Bake on cookie sheet at
turning	2
to 3 times until crisp, about 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: easy "no fail" macaroni and cheese
directions: *Any kind or combination of 1%, 2%, whole, canned evaporated or powdered. I usually use 2% with a little powdered.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Make Crust:
Combine the cooked spaghetti, garlic, butter, Parmesan cheese, egg and basil.
Mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package only shorten the length of time.
Mix with the onion soup and sour cream; pour into casserole.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top and add paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet and drain.
Cut cabbage in casserole dish.
Pour ground beef and onion on top of cabbage; add rice, tomato soup and water in skillet and mix well.
Pour over cabbage and beef mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: spiced cranberry-orange mold
directions: Finely chop cranberries in blender or food processor container; mix with sugar.
Set aside.
Stir boiling water into gelatin and salt in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water, juice, cinnamon and cloves. Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in cranberries, orange and nuts.
Spoon into 5-cup mold which has been lightly sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients and mix alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melts in your mouth.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch well-greased pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Cool this mixture and add peaches.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients at one time.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom of pan only).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk, sugar and vanilla together with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into a prepared 9 x 13-inch graham cracker crust.
Top with 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and boil mushrooms for 15 to 20 minutes; drain.
Cut onion into chunks.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, oregano and salt. Combine with mushrooms and onion.
Marinate 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: three cheese chicken casserole
directions: Bring water, salt and oil to a boil. Slowly add noodles. Return to a boil. Cook 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain and set aside.

title: linguine tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, onions and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add hot linguine; toss.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter until very soft.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Mix in vanilla and almond extract.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: alice's upside-down cake
