directions: Mix coconut and pecans and spread evenly in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the cake mix according to package directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.

In a saucepan, melt butter with cream cheese; heat until it is soft enough to whip in the powdered sugar. Spoon evenly over cake batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat; add tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Place a layer of meat mixture in bowl.
Add a layer of corn chips, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat with meat mixture, corn chips and top with cheese.
Use onions, if preferred.

title: finger lickin' chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients (cracker crumbs and spices).
Dip chicken pieces into evaporated milk and then roll in dry ingredients.
Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered pan and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate yams; add eggs and mix well.
Add sugar, salt and spices; mix thoroughly.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Bake in greased baking dish 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: potatoes in sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Put in 9 x 9 pan or baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Follow basic biscuit recipe, roll dough about 1/4 inch thick and cut with a doughnut cutter. Dip biscuit in melted butter and then in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Twist once, piece on lightly greased baking sheet about 1 inch apart. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Shape into balls and refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Melt the dipping chocolate in a double boiler.
Dip balls one at a time and set on waxed paper to set.
Store in cool dry place.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator until partially set.
Then add Cool Whip and whip together.
Put back in refrigerator.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water according to directions on box. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Mix lemonade according to directions on can. Mix orange juice according to directions on can. Stir thoroughly. Taste. Add more sugar if needed.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: bit o' spice prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add cooked prunes.
Add nuts (optional).
Bake at 330° until done.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and pineapple together until rhubarb is tender. Remove from heat and add Jello. Place in jars and seal.

title: jezebel cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake.
Let cool.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let soak into cake holes, then pour caramel topping over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: fudge date bars
directions: Mix hot water, soda and dates and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and cocoa.
Blend well.
Add date mixture and put in greased bar pan (10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle on chips and nuts and a little sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into jelly roll pan.
Bake cookie dough until lightly browned at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie dough.
Top with your favorite fresh fruits.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in Italian dressing.
Mix other ingredients and roll chicken in mixture.
Spray pan with Pam and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until tender.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.
Serve with tortilla chips, as side dish with meals, on tacos and with cheese dip.

title: creamy ranch potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Stir in soup.
Add to potatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or on high for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.
Stir to blend before serving.

title: cottage cheese zucchini bake
directions: Slice and parboil zucchini for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs with cottage cheese, seasoning and Cheddar cheese.
Mix with zucchini and place in casserole.
Top with a little more cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: party fudge bars
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and Coffee Rich in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in marshmallows and chips.
Heat until melted. Cover and set aside.

title: potato moussaka
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Brush lightly with oil and broil 5 minutes on each side.
Arrange half of potatoes in an even layer in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Saute onion in olive oil.
Set aside.

title: susan's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered (greased) casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until top is brown.
Good!!!

title: mom's chocolate candy
directions: Pour sugar, margarine, milk mixture over top and mix gently until well mixed.
Spread in buttered pan.
Let stand until hard. Cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.
Great for Christmas.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes or until light and golden.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine together.
Add flour, salt, pepper and cereal.
Form small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press into wafers with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Preheat
oven to 400°.	Lightly grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll
pan.	Slice
peaches	1/4-inch thick into a large bowl (4 cup).
Add lemon juice;
toss to coat.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Stir together cereal and milk.
Let stand about 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.

title: fudge
directions: In large pan, melt butter, then add sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Turn down, but still boiling, and stir.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream and morsels.
Mix well with mixer, then pour in buttered dish.
Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Boil beef for 1 1/2 to 2 hours; drain.
Cut green pepper, red pepper, pineapple and onions into squares.
Place on bamboo skewers, a piece of beef, green pepper, red pepper, pineapple and onion.
Repeat this step as often as needed.
Leave approximately 1 1/2 inches on side of bamboo skewers (for handling).
Repeat process for each bamboo skewer.
Place in oven or on a grill for 15 to 25 minutes.
Marinate with barbecue sauce.
Put back in oven or on grill for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Cook the eggs, lemon juice and powdered sugar and cool.
Stir constantly until thick.
When cool, pour over fruit and macaroni mixture.
Let stand overnight. Before serving, add 1 cup Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: english muffins
directions: Heat milk and lard in a medium-size saucepan just until lard is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.

title: deer hash
directions: Cook meat in a pressure cooker until tender.
Shred meat. Add to broth with onions, sage and dried pepper (red).
When it has cooked down until almost all broth has gone, add small diced potatoes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes; blend well with butter and sugar (medium speed with electric mixer).
Fold in Bisquick (low speed). Should dough appear too moist due to the difference in consistency of sweet potatoes, add a little more Bisquick.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch biscuits. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: texas stew
directions: Throw all in crock-pot and cook until done.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk and corn.
Blend well and pour in casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine on top and bake at 350° until almost firm.

title: no bake tangy cherry pie
directions: Blend all ingredients (except pie filling) in a bowl.
Pour evenly in 2 pie shells.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Pour pie filling evenly on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until tender.

title: asparagus, chicken casserole
directions: Pour liquid off asparagus into soup; blend well.
Line a greased dish with asparagus.
Layer chicken, cheese and egg slices.
Pour soup mixture over.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix flour, sugar and juice until smooth; add cheese.
Spread pineapple in bottom of dish and cover with cheese mixture.
Mix margarine and crackers and spread on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter, sugars, peanut butter, egg and vanilla for 2 minutes on high. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl.
Add dry ingredients to mixture. Stir on "fold and dry" to moisten ingredients.
Mix on high for 1 minute.
Roll about 2 teaspoons of mixture in a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out cookie shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions and let cool. Combine water and cornstarch and stir until dissolved.
Add dry jello and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Set aside and cool.
After cooled, add sliced strawberries and pour into cooled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mama's divinity
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and water.
Cook on medium heat to soft ball stage.
Pour 1/2 of syrup mixture gradually into egg whites, beating constantly.
Reheat syrup a few seconds while beating. Beat until mixture begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and pecans. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: In a large bowl, mix faith, patience and sympathy.
Blend in forgiveness, kindness and courage.
Pour into a heart of joy. Sprinkle with harmony.
Top with a spread of understanding. Sweeten with respect and bake in an oven of trust.
Serve with a tender smile.

title: crock pot magic venison meat loaf
directions: Mix the egg, milk, salt and bread crumbs and allow to soften. Thoroughly combine with ground venison and chopped vegetables. Shape into a loaf and place into crock pot.
Top with catsup and green pepper rings.
Place potatoes along side of the loaf.
(If potatoes are peeled, coat them with butter.)
Cover and set on high for 1 hour.
Turn down to low for 8 to 9 hours.
This may be doubled for 5 quart crock pots.

title: lemon truffle pie
directions: In medium saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch and flour; mix well.

title: chicken biscuit casserole
directions: Blend soup and 1/2 cup milk in skillet; add next 4 ingredients. Heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Pour into 1-quart casserole. Combine biscuit mix and 1/3 cup milk. Drop by spoonfuls onto hot chicken mixture. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned. Yield: 4 servings.

title: fettuccine supreme
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter on low speed.
Add basil, parsley and pepper.
Add boiling water, mix well and set aside. Boil noodles until done.
Rinse and drain noodles; saute garlic in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Toss with noodles.
Toss noodles with cheese and herb mixture and add Parmesan cheese.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together Crisco and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly. Stir in M&M's candies and nuts.

title: whole wheat stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers to make boats.
Dice pulp and reserve.
Cook zucchini boats in boiling water for 3 minutes or until almost tender; drain.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: mixed fruit pies
directions: Add to heated cherries 1 cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons of flour or cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Add to heated pineapple 1 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of flour or cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Cool both mixtures, then combine and add oranges and pecans.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed, except add eggs and mandarin oranges.
Bake in four 8 or 9-inch round floured and greased pans. Bake for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from cake pans and let cool.

title: melt-in-your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add to sugar-shortening mixture the vanilla and egg. Beat and slowly add dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple whiskey cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lined with wax paper at 350° for 1 hour.
Five minutes before cake is done, simmer 1 stick butter (not margarine) with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup whiskey. When cake is done, pour half of whiskey mixture over cake.
Twenty minutes later, pour remainder of mixture over cake.
Cool cake completely in pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease skillet. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter, then powdered sugar.
Add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs and roll into balls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and put aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well blended. Stir in zucchini and pecans.
Add dry ingredients, mixing until just moistened.
Spoon batter into loaf pans or 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream cheese and pecans, if desired.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; set aside.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Fill jar up with cucumbers (sliced), then add dried mustard, sugar, salt and turmeric.
Fill jars with cold vinegar.
Seal and shake once in a while for 2 or 3 days.

title: mom's ginger bread
directions: *To make moderately stiff batter.

title: nutcracker nuggets
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour and nuts to make soft dough.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill 2 hours.

title: robin's corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chilies and cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into long casserole.
Slice chilies and layer over mixture.
Layer 1/2 cheese, then remaining corn mixture and chilies.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Firm, but not dry.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet bowknots(italian)
directions: Beat eggs lightly, add granulated sugar, salt and flavoring. Blend thoroughly.
Place flour on board; cut in butter and add egg mixture.
Knead until smooth dough is obtained.
If dough is too soft, gradually add a little flour to make firm, but not hard. Set aside for 30 minutes.
Then cut dough into 4 sections.
Roll on well-floured board until wafer thin.
Cut with pastry cutter into strips 6 inches long x 3/4-inch wide.
Tie individual bowknots or make slit in center and invert.
Fry bows about 3 minutes unti lightly
brown in deep hot oil.
Drain on absorbent paper, cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen bowknots.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar in electric skillet.
Set control at 280°.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, margarine, softened cream cheese and sugars; mix well until creamy and light.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach-chicken dumplings
directions: Place spinach into boiling water until it softens (10 to 15 minutes).
Then put spinach into cold water to cool.
When cool, wring out extra water.
Then chop finely.
Mix spinach with salt, pepper, cornstarch, oil, chicken and egg.
Moisten edges of individual pasta wraps lightly.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture on each moistened pasta wrap.
Fold the pasta wraps in half and crinkle the remaining edges to enclose the mixture.
Then put dumplings into a nonstick pan with 1 cup cold water for about 15 minutes or until the water evaporates.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes on low in oil.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald Sego and whole milk in saucepan.
Mix salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Add milk; bring to boil.
Pour a little milk mixture into eggs, stirring constantly.
Add egg mixture to milk and thicken.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add rice and raisins.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: In deep skillet, melt butter, add sugar, salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, cored side down.
Cover, cook gently 5 minutes. Carefully turn tomatoes.
Add last four ingredients to sauce. Cook uncovered 5 more minutes, spooning mixture in pan over top. Spoon extra sauce on top and serve hot.

title: camp coffee
directions: Bring cold water to a boil.
Blend egg with coffee.
Stir mixture into boiling water.
Steep (don't boil) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked crab spread
directions: Rinse crab meat with water.
Drain and squeeze out excess water.
Mix crab and cream cheese until creamy.
Mix in additional ingredients, onion and Mozzarella.
Spread mixture in pie plate. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for at least 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with crackers!

title: garlic sauce(scordalia)
directions: Place minced garlic, potatoes and salt in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Slowly add oil, alternating with vinegar (or lemon juice).
Blend until smooth.
If sauce is too thick, thin with several tablespoons of water.
Serve on fried codfish, green beans, boiled beets, fried eggplant, squash, etc.
Also use as a fresh vegetable dip.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In the a.m., remove Potato Flakes Herman starter from the refrigerator.
Add sugar, instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water. is regulating or feeding the starter; regulate every 3 to 7 days.) Mix well and let stand out of refrigerator all day (with cheesecloth cover).

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Crush brickle bits in baggie with rolling pin; blender makes them too fine.
Combine all ingredients, except pecans and beat for 2 minutes.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into two well-greased and floured 4x9-inch loaf pans.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of melted butter.
Smash in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool thoroughly.
Whip 2 sticks of margarine, eggs and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Spread over other mix.
Slice bananas lengthwise.
Lay bananas on crust mixture and put pineapple on top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Stir in butter or margarine into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spread into pan. Cover with cottage cheese.
In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and pepper.
Cook until ground beef is browned, then drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Heat through.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: small italian cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature for best results. Grease and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Stage 1:
Mix Worcestershire, liquid smoke, hot sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder in large container.
Place meat in container and marinate in refrigerator for a minimum of 12 hours.

title: ranch stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out inside of baked potatoes and combine with sour cream and dressing mix.
Fill potato skins with mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: fitz's gorgonzola dressing
directions: Cheese is best if frozen first.
Thoroughly combine all ingredients except cheese.
Blend in cheese last.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and vegetables.
Combine sugar and tomato sauce and add to browned mixture.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour over cooked pasta.

title: fricidillie
directions: Tear bread into small bits and add to meat with salt and pepper.
Add eggs and milk and mix well.
(Mixture will be very soft.)
Melt shortening in a skillet.
Drop in meat mixture by teaspoonfuls.
Brown on both sides.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 box German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour on top of pecan mixture.
In saucepan, put one stick of margarine and 8 ounces of cream cheese, softened.
Heat until mixture is warm enough to stir in one box confectioners sugar (1 pound).
Spoon over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until cooled.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy saucepan add sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage (275°).
Then add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat and add margarine and baking soda.
Beat well and pour onto a well-buttered cookie sheet. Break into pieces.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, cheese, parsley, onion, egg yolks and 1/2 cup melted butter in mixing bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan; stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk gradually, stirring until well.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in ungreased 9x13 inch pan at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen delicious brownies!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan the drained sauerkraut (add caraway seed, if desired) and sliced tomatoes over top of kraut.
Dot each tomato with Thousand Island dressing.
Next, put thin slices of turkey sausage or turkey kielbasa on top of this.
Cover and bake about 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Put back in oven and let melt some.
Make rye crumbs from toasted rye bread or rye crackers. Toss with a little melted butter and sprinkle over melted cheese. Sprinkle on some more cheese and allow to brown in oven.

title: apple "fritters"
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into 1/2-inch rings.
Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Make a well in the center; add sugar and egg in the well.
Starting from the center, mix egg into flour slowly, adding milk until the batter is smooth.
Dip the apple rings into batter and deep fry in very hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 2-quart round casserole. In large bowl, with fork, mix flour and next 4 ingredients.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissors fashion, cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.

title: teriyaki canapes
directions: Remove all fat and cut steak into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over the meat.
Let stand at least two hours, or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat until fluffy the eggs, vanilla, oil and sugar.
Add in order: zucchini, flour, salt, soda, baking powder, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and bake in two loaf pans that are greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer 1/2 of cake, cubed, 1/2 of pudding mix, 1 can of strawberry pie filling, 1/2 pineapple (drained) and 1/2 Cool Whip. Repeat layers.
Make in a large punch bowl and top with chopped nuts.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together and stir only until well blended.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter with sugar.
Add beaten eggs, raisins and milk.
Mix well and combine with flour.
Add vanilla; beat thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls into greased baking sheets.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 12 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cooked ground beef, refried beans and taco seasoning. Layer in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Combine sour cream with bottle of taco sauce.
Layer on the meat mixture and cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: "60" sec chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate, egg and vanilla in blender or food processor. Heat cream in small saucepan over medium heat until small bubbles form around edge.
With machine running, add hot cream.
Blend until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth, about 1 minute. Pour mousse into bowl.
Cool slightly.
Cover with plastic wrap. Chill 2 to 3 hours or until set.
Serve in wine glasses or small dessert dishes topped with whipped cream.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add plums and all other ingredients; beat well.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put in paper sack and close real tight.
Ready to eat.

title: "p" nut butter fudge(single batch)
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook on high until dissolved.
Turn down on medium.
Cook until hard ball forms in cold water.
Add peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Remove from heat.
Hand beat until hard.
Butter the pan or dish before pouring fudge in it.

title: easy bars
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Melt butter and honey and add with vanilla to dry mixture. Mix. Press into 10 X 15 jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Remove from oven. Spoon peanut butter in globs over bars and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Cover the pan and when peanut butter and chips are soft, spread evenly to frost. Cut while warm.

title: mock pralines
directions: Cook 2 minutes the butter, margarine and sugar, stirring well. Add pecans; stir.
Pour over 16 graham crackers which should be lining a cookie sheet that has sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: In 2-quart microproof bowl, cook beef on High for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Drain and add sauce, water and salt; mix well.
In 11 x 7-inch baking dish, arrange half of uncooked lasagna noodles over 1/3 sauce.
Use 1/3 Mozzarella cheese on top of that and repeat.
After the third layer of sauce, top with Parmesan cheese. Save the last 1/3 Mozzarella cheese for later.
Cover with wrap and cook 30 minutes or until noodles are soft.
Remove from microwave and top with last part of Mozzarella cheese.
Cook 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat egg. Add milk and melted fat. Add to dry ingredients. Beat until smooth. Stir in corn.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Fry in fat until golden brown.

title: cocoa-lite angel food cake
directions: Prepare egg white mixture as directed on package. Combine contents of cake flour mixture with cocoa until well blended and continue as directed on package.
Bake according to directions on package.

title: hamburger-scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Set aside.
Make white sauce of next 5 ingredients.
Place half of the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the meat, half the sauce and half the onions.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: joe's quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, bell peppers and garlic. Drain. Place in large pan and add
seasonings,
tomato
paste and water. Beans may also be added if you want.
Joe uses red kidney beans. Simmer for 1/2 hour or so.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash over low heat until tender; drain well.
Beat eggs; stir into squash with milk, crumbs, cheese and chilies. Spread in a 10-inch casserole dish which has been sprayed.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into large bowl. Combine oleo, cocoa and water in pan and cook to boiling. Pour over sugar and flour and mix. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and mix well. (It will be thin.) Pour into greased jelly roll pan, 15 x 10-inches. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Prepare icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Add minced onions and fry lightly. Add vinegar, sugar and seasoning.
Let come to a boil and pour over sliced potatoes.
Mix well.
Garnish with parsley and sliced hard-boiled eggs.

title: monster cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix together peanut butter, margarine, sugars, soda and vanilla thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8-inch or 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and water.
Mix sugar, flour, oats, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Clean chicken pieces and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix sour cream, sherry and mushroom soup together.
Pour sauce over chicken pieces placed far apart.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (or longer at a lower heat).

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown meat; then drain the grease from the meat.
The next step you do is to add the bell pepper, onion and bay leaves until vegetables are tender.
After the vegetables are tender, then add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer about 30 minutes on low heat.
When the chili is almost done, add the wieners to the chili and let cook for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: heart healthy fish dish
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Coat fish with cornstarch and brown in oil 3 minutes per side.
Remove fish; keep warm.
Stir tomatoes, green beans, mushrooms, soy sauce and oregano in same pan.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until beans are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Arrange fish in sauce and vegetables.
Heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: summertime broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Cook bacon until crispy. Break bacon into small pieces and mix with broccoli.

title: cherry cheese tarts for 24
directions: Line medium muffin paper cups with a vanilla wafer in each bottom of a cup.
Combine ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Fill cups 2/3 full of cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Chill and then top before serving with any fruit mixture for pies.

title: mildred's guess again cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, potato chips and nuts.
Mix well. Drop by scant teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Put it in the microwave.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine 2 cups graham crackers, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar; mix well and press into a 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Cook at 325° for 5 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: ladyfinger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into "fingers".
Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes.
Cool on rack, then cover with additional powdered sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix butter, soup and sour cream together.
Mix together with frozen hash brown potatoes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses cream taffy
directions: Mix molasses and sugar in a saucepan and bring to boiling point.
Add the thick cream, reduce flame to low heat (265°) and continue cooking until a sample makes a hard ball when put in cold water.
Add the soda and beat until thick.
Pour onto a buttered platter.
As edges cool, turn into center.
When cool enough to handle, pull until light colored and stiff enough to hold its shape.
Cut into small pieces.

title: pizza
directions: Put crust first.
Then sauce.
Then cheese, then put into the oven.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions, peppers, and garlic. Cover with ice and let stand 3 hours. Drain. Add other ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil for 2
minutes. Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: butter bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Add eggs and beat a bit.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into muffin papers.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crazy corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/2 teaspoons butter.
Melt cheese in 2 cups milk, stirring constantly.
Then stir in 6 cups milk, bouillon cubes and 1/4 cup butter.
Cook until well mixed.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot, except noodles.
Cook until done. Add 1/2 pound egg noodles and cook 15 minutes.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut apples in half. Peel, core and slice apples and place in baking dish. Combine cake mix, sugar, cinnamon, butter and nuts in a bowl. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping, if desired.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain.
Add corn, catsup, barbecue and chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: aunt jan's brisket
directions: Use 3 salts to salt the brisket heavily.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over brisket.
Seal tightly with foil. Cook at 225° for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove from oven and pour off liquid.
Cool liquid and remove fat.
Let meat cool, remove fat, slice and return to baking dish.
Pour sauce over meat, cover with foil and heat at 350° until hot.

title: mexican spread (chip dip)
directions: Rinse peppers and
place
under
broiler
on top shelf. Blacken all sides.	Place
into
paper bag after blackened and let rest for 20
minutes.
On
a
plate
peel skin off, remove stem and seeds, and save liquid that collects on plate.	Slice peppers into 1/8
x
1/2-inch
slices.
Place
in
a dish that complements the pepper color and add liquid from plate.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil
and
cloves garlic (must use a garlic press); taste. Add more garlic or oil if desired.
Serve on a platter with goat cheese and Melba toast onion rounds.

title: easy seafood bombay
directions: In the microwave, heat soup and milk thoroughly.
Add cooked seafood and curry and heat again.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening. Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Yield 20-25 servings.

title: baked breaded corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar and flour together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt margarine; crumb slices of bread in.
Mix well.
Pour over top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple, raisin, walnut cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs together until foamy; add sugar and vanilla. Continue to beat.
Add apples, beating slightly; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins and walnuts to flour mixture.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, beating slightly. Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Check for doneness in 60 minutes.
This is a heavy cake, so may take longer.

title: chili con carne
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook in salted water, following directions on package, about 1 hour or until tender.
Heat olive oil over low flame in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add meat, stirring frequently until it loses red color.
Add onion, garlic, sweet pepper, bay leaf, oregano, chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper, black pepper, paprika and chili pods.
Stir well. Cover pan and saute about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, blending well.

title: lasagna presto
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together until beef is brown.
Add garlic, oregano, soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: beef manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti as directed; drain and place on foil in a single layer.
Cook and drain ground beef.
Mix all ingredients with beef.
Stuff pasta.
Add in a single layer in a baking dish. Spoon 1/2 cup tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: coconut cake
directions: Place sour cream, sugar and coconut in bowl overnight.
Follow Duncan Hines Deluxe white cake mix (use oil or butter or margarine).
Let cool.
Slice layers to make 4.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash and sort peas.
Soak in cold water overnight.
Drain. Place in soup kettle with onion, celery, garlic and cold water. Cover.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer about 4 hours.
When meat is tender, remove and cool.
Skim fat from soup.
Add carrots, seasonings and diced ham.
Cook until carrots are done.
If soup is too thick, thin with a little water or chicken broth.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut unpeeled potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Peel garlic clove and cut lengthwise in half. In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat potatoes, garlic and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat to
low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are very tender.
Drain. Return potatoes and garlic to saucepan. With potato masher, mash potatoes and garlic with milk and salt until smooth.
Stir in chopped parsley.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Salt
and
pepper
meat.
Mix
in corn flakes and soup. Put in loaf
pan and pour ketchup over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half into greased skillet.
Add half of cheese.
Pour remaining ingredients and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Boil meat in salted water about 1 hour.
Remove scum from water and keep boiling.
Cut up vegetables and add to boiling meat.
Cook about 2 hours.
Keep adding water.
Serve with noodles or dumplings.

title: mary's microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 4-quart microwavable bowl, mix sugar, milk and butter. Cook on High 20 to 25 minutes or until a few drops in cold water form a ball.
Stir every 5 minutes while cooking.
Stir in chips and marshmallow cream.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 7 x 12-inch (or appropriate size) buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Recipe can be halved, following same directions except cook 13 to 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased bread pans.
Bake 1 - 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees, in middle rack of oven.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Mix cream cheese and Miracle Whip, then mix in ice cream.
Add the fruit cocktail and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan. Freeze for several hours.
Serve fast, as it melts quick.

title: ann's refrigerator rolls
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a pan on stove and scald.
(Do not boil.)
After this, cool to lukewarm (Ann puts in water with ice cubes).
While cooling mixture, dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine milk mixture with yeast (everything is baby lukewarm).
Add this to bowl of mixer and then add flour (plain, White Lily) until consistency of thin cake batter.
Cover with thin towel and store in warm place. Let rise for 2 hours.
Go back to mixer and add 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Knead or use mixer on low speed until all is absorbed.
Put in Tupperware container and put in refrigerator.
Roll out 2 hours before baking and let rise.
Try not to work in excess flour when rolling out.
Put in muffin tins. Brush with melted butter and bake at 400°.
They will be done in about 10 minutes.

title: pecan dream bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat Eagle Brand milk, 1 egg and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans and baking chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: what's in it salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients over heat until
marshmallows have melted.
Remove from heat. Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Allow to set until it begins to congeal. Fold in mayonnaise, whipped cream, pineapple, cabbage and nutmeats.
Mix carefully, but well. Place in an 8 x 8-inch dish or pan. Cover with Saran or foil. Refrigerate.
Serves 9.
Delicious!

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburg; add seasoning.
Cook noodles and beans and put in layers.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Mix slightly.

title: yellow hard pea soup(ertesuppe)
directions: Soak peas in water, covered, overnight.
Wash and clean meats. Let soak overnight, each in their own bowl.
Next day in large kettle, add peas and the meat with water to cover.
Bring to boil and skim off.
Cover; let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once in awhile.
Add onions, celery, parsnips, rutabaga and carrots, which have been peeled and cut into small pieces.
Cook and stir frequently.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add 3 teaspoons thyme leaves when almost done.

title: beef broccoli wellington
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet brown meat; drain.
Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well and simmer 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
On ungreased cookie sheet, overlap long sides of 2 rectangles 1/2 inch; press edges to seal.
Press it to form 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spoon meat mixture in 3-inch strip lengthwise down center of dough.
Bring long edges over mixture.
Seal it by pinching dough together.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter ice cream #2
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into ice cream churn that has been prepared with ice and salt.
Add milk to fill line of churn.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped green pepper, onion, tomatoes or whatever you desire.

title: cheese carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots and onion in salted water.
Drain.
Melt cheese and butter together.
Mix and bake in a casserole at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old tea cake recipe
directions: Mix all together to make tea cakes.
Roll out like biscuits. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: apple-pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg slightly.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Serve with whipped cream.

title: beef patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Shape in patties.
Fry in skillet until done.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup with 1 can water.
Pour over patties.
Either, cover and bake in microwave for about 10 minutes or bake in conventional oven for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Make sure soup is bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend first 9 ingredients, low speed until moistened, then for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour half of batter into pan.
In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture and chocolate chips over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter, sugar mixture and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with ice cream to serve.

title: no-fat fried spinach
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick butter flavor spray.
Add spinach and stir-fry 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until spinach softens. Add soy sauce and cook another minute.

title: salt risen bread
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in quart jar.
Add corn meal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Pour warm water and scalded milk over mixture.
Put lid on jar.
Place jar in electric oven.
Turn control just until oven clicks on.
Let stand overnight or 12 to 15 hours, until contents are fermented.
Remove potatoes from starter and make the sponge.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate salad for 4 to 6 hours or overnight in the mixture of mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar, then add bacon.
Keep cold.

title: jewish bar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: sticky buns
directions: Mix milk, shortening, sugar, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat with spoon.
Add yeast and egg.
Add rest of flour; let rise until double.
Punch down.
Roll; spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Slice 1-inch thick and put in pan on top of Sticky Goo.
Let rise until Goo cannot be seen.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out and let rest 1 minute; turn upside-down on cookie sheet.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve immediately or refrigerate overnight.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and nuts.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Lay out the crackers.
Spread the mixture as evenly as possible.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut in half while warm.
Cool completely before storing.
(Watch carefully, they burn easily.)

title: rhubarb-date pudding
directions: Cook rhubarb and dates in water for 5-8 minutes. Add sugar, crumbs and butter. Bake in a greased 1-quart casserole at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or other topping. Serves 4.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add egg.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough well.
Form in small ball the size of a walnut, flatten with a fork dipped in flour to make a crisscross design.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand in refrigerator overnight. Serves 6 to 8.
Keeps well for a long time.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, lemon rind and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into loaf pan that has been greased and lined on bottom of pan with wax paper (cut to make it fit).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Line a large electric skillet with foil.
Combine sugar, water, syrup and margarine on skillet.
Set temperature at 375°.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until syrup turns golden brown.
Stir in peanuts.
Continue stirring until mixture turns medium brown.
Add soda.
Stir vigorously.
Remove foil containing candy from skillet and let cool.
Remove sheet of candy from foil and break into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon in crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, baking soda, and salt. Cream butter, add sugar. Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir until thoroughly mixed. Stir in mashed bananas. Fold in dry ingredients. Spray 2 small loaf pans with Pam. Pour in mixture. Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken, then soup mixture.
Layer 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Layer 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Put 1/2 stick oleo in parts on top.
Bake at 350° close to 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.

title: taco munch snack mix
directions: Toss popcorn, cereal squares and pretzels in large bowl. Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter and taco seasoning; drizzle over popcorn mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and toss to coat; cool.
Store in airtight container.
Just before serving, toss with Cheddar cheese.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple with well beaten eggs.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together and add to the egg and pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm and brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and chopped onion; reserve.
Mix baking mix and water until a soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up on sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes, onion and green pepper in dish.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with your choice of taco sauce.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add carrots, potatoes, bouillon and 1 cup of water.
Simmer until cooked.
Add corn, milk, cheese and flour, mixed with milk to thicken.
Heat until hot; do not boil.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, can of tomato paste, water, bay leaf, nutmeg and sugar. Simmer.

title: creamed cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots in salted water.
In shortening, brown onion and parsley greens.
Add paprika and flour.
Add to soup slowly.
Bring to a boil.
Make small dumplings from one egg and add to soup, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: old fashioned low-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Cream sugars and Butter Buds.
Add egg whites, oats, flour, soda, spices and vanilla.
Stir until smooth; then add raisins and water.
Stir.
Chill, if needed, or add a little extra flour.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 17 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: In a bowl, beat sugar with butter until it looks creamy.
In another bowl, beat the eggs strongly for 3 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate with the milk over hot water.
Add eggs and chocolate mixture to the butter, mixing well each time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add this slowly into the batter.
Add the vanilla and last, add the chopped walnuts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1/4 cup water in top of double boiler. Blend. Stir in gelatin mixture.
Place over boiling water.
Beat constantly with rotary beater until thick and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool well.

title: broccoli, tomato and basil frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil a 7 or 8-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Saute onion for 5 minutes.
Add tomato and basil and saute 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add broccoli and mushrooms and cook 5 minutes more. Add this mixture to eggs and pour into prepared dish.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes until set.
Serve immediately.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix together and spread on bottom of 9 inch pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients over bean mixture. Refrigerate and serve with warm tortilla chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble beef in microwavable bowl.
Heat on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine cheese, egg and pepper.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Place apples and dry ingredients in bowl. Toss to coat well. Pour into casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch
baking pan coated with Pam.
Coat chops with Shake 'N Bake and arrange on top of apples. Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: greek stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook frozen spinach on high until barely defrosted.
Drain in colander, pressing out moisture.
In mixing bowl, combine spinach, cheeses, onion, parsley and salt to taste.
Mix well.
Mound mushroom caps high with spinach mixture.
Arrange on serving plate and cook on high until steaming, approximately 3 to 4 minutes. Spinach mixture may be formed into balls and frozen to be placed in mushroom caps just before microwaving.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and molasses in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow.
Pour into 8x8 buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: blueberry crunch coffee ring
directions: In a well-greased and flour dusted 9-inch spring-form pan, pat about 1/2 of Walnut Streusel in an even layer and set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together at one time.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: june's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and margarine until like sand crumbs.
Add just enough water to hold together.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Make a topping of 1 stick margarine and 1/4 pound saltine crackers, crushed. Brown under broiler.
Can be heated in microwave.

title: hanky panks(makes 40)
directions: Mix meat, brown and drain.
Melt cheese in skillet.
Add spices, return meat to skillet and blend.
Spread on rye.
Can be frozen.
Heat under broiler until cheese bubbles and turns brown.

title: desert inn cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes or until cool. Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; add to oats mixture. Sift together dry ingredients and add to oats mixture; mix well. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and add the spice ball.
Cook 1 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir often until mixture is to desired thickness.
Remove spice ball and can.

title: caroler's punch
directions: Stir honey into hot tea until well blended.
Cool and chill. Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
At serving time, combine tea and honey mixture with fruit juices in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add ice cubes.
Makes about 35 servings.

title: crispy carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Place carrots in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Stir in onion; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats. Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Mix all other ingredients together, then mix in oats. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, prepare rice as label directs; set aside.
Discard tough green outer leaves from cabbage; with sharp knife, remove core.
Fill 8-quart sauce pot three-fourths full with water; heat to boiling.
Place cabbage in water, cut side up.
Using 2 large spoons or forks, gently separate leaves as outer leaves soften slightly; remove 8 large leaves from cabbage and let drain on paper towels.
Coarsely shred remaining cabbage; set aside.
Trim rib of each reserved leaf very thin.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, onion, salt and pepper until meat is browned, stirring often. Stir in rice and 1 1/2 cups marinara sauce.
On center of each cabbage leaf, place about 1/2 cupful ground beef mixture.
Fold 2 sides of cabbage leaf over meat, overlapping edges,; roll jelly roll fashion.
Evenly sprinkle shredded cabbage in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place stuffed cabbage rolls, seam side down, on cabbage in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over cabbage rolls; cover dish with foil.
Bake in 350° oven 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender, basting often with sauce in dish.
Makes 8 servings, 350 calories per serving.

title: medley marinade
directions: Mix drained vegetables.
Mix dressing until sugar is dissolved. Pour over vegetables.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour over chicken wings (5 pounds). Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
Put layer of potatoes on bottom. Put onions over potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Place chicken on top with skin side up.
Salt and pepper.
Spread soup over chicken.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Uncover and brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on with bay leaf and cook until tender.
Cool, then peel.
Shred potatoes into an oblong baking dish.
Mix soup, onion and sour cream in a mixing bowl.
Cover potatoes with mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or little less.
Don't burn.
can put in microwave for 15 minutes, but watch the cheese.
tags: cream of celery soup (cream of mushroom is better

title: state sausage and bean combo
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan or slow cooker.
Add enough of the saved vegetable water to ingredients so it won't stick or burn.
Heat through until flavors blend.
If cooked too long, the potatoes will become mushy.
Serve with hot bread!
Good!

title: russian balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar, gradually add in flour.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 min.
DO NOT BROWN.
Roll in Confectionor's Sugar, let cool and roll in sugar again.
Makes 2 - 2 1\2 Doz.

title: cement pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Fold in crushed crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cool, top with whipped cream and sprinkle with additional chopped nuts.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.

Sift half of the flour, the salt and baking powder together and add to milk and egg mixture. Beat smooth and add only as much more flour as needed to make batter thin enough to run through a funnel into deep, hot fat. Spirals and other shapes can be made by controlling spout with finger.
Serve hot with molasses, jelly or powdered sugar.

title: pink dip
directions: With hand mixer, mix cream cheese and sauce together until smooth.
If you want it more spicy, add more sauce.
Now break out your favorite chip or vegetable and dip away.
Our favorite is nacho cheese tortilla chips.

title: corn bread(very moist)]
directions: If you don't have sour milk, add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar to sweet milk and allow to sit a few minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together juices.
Add ginger ale and sherbet before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana-berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water. Chill until
slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Stir
in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until
firm,
about
15 minutes.
Whisk pudding into
milk.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Stir in remaining strawberries.
Spread mixture over gelatin in pie crust.
Chill until
set,
about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional sliced strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix 2/3 cup water, 1/4 cup salsa, 1 tablespoon butter and stuffing mix.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with deboned chicken.
Pour remaining salsa over chicken and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cut the broccoli into uniform 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Steam until just beginning to become tender, but not cooked through.
Remove from heat; allow to cool and chop into bite size pieces.
Beat together the cream and eggs.
Add the cheeses, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in the broccoli.
Pour the mixture into a buttered, shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned on top.
This is better if made up the day before baking and serving.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar and crushed pineapple together.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Punch holes in cake and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Mix instant vanilla pudding by directions.
Then add sour cream, mix together then spread over the pineapple mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake, then sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and keep covered in refrigerator.
Serve with ham or for an appetizer, spoon over cube of cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: stuffed fresh mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine.
Fry bacon crisp. Saute stems and onion in bacon drippings.
Drain off most of the grease.
In a bowl, mix bacon and all other ingredients except butter.
Stuff this mixture into caps; pour butter over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mystery cheese cake pie
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top of mixture.
In bowl, combine 2 eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, Karo syrup, maple flavoring and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and carefully pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: natural egg dyes
directions: Fill coffee cups half full with any of the ingredients.
Dye boiled eggs in cups.
For golden color, simmer dry outer skin of onions in an equal amount of water for 10 minutes or longer.
For blue, mash blueberries (fresh, canned or frozen) in a pan.
Add enough water to make a liquid.
Simmer 10 minutes or longer.
For yellow, simmer celery leaves 10 minutes or longer.
For purple, use strong grape juice, and for brown, use coffee or tea.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Combine sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda and egg in a bowl with cheese and yeast mixture.
Add flour to form stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Stir down dough. Turn into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or 8-inch round pan. Let rise 30 to 40 minutes or until light.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Roll in balls, then in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Roll in more powdered sugar.

title: speedy goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Gradually add macaroni.
Simmer uncovered about 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring frequently to keep macaroni from sticking.
Add more water if necessary. Serve garnished with parsley.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs and molasses.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, then add to cream mixture.
Roll into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: no cook peach pie
directions: Crumble thick layer of cookies in bottom of casserole.
Mix pudding by package directions and spread over crumbs.
Spread peaches over pudding and spread layer of Cool Whip over peaches. Sprinkle cookie crumbs over cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: boursin chicken
directions: Flour chicken with herbs.
Cook bacon in large frying pan. Save enough bacon fat in pan to cover bottom of pan.
Saute chicken in fat until golden.
Layer bacon on the chicken with a dollop of Boursin.
Cover pan until the cheese is melted.
Serve with rice and salad.
So easy and elegant.

title: basic "baker's clay"(non-edible)
directions: In a
large
flat bottomed bowl mix flour and salt with rubber spatula
or
wooden spoon.	Add water slowly, mixing as you pour. Additional	water
may
be	needed depending on the humidity of the weather.
However, use caution in adding more water as	the dough
should
be
very stiff for best results. Knead for
10 minutes.
Dough
is
ready	to use when texture appears soft
and smooth.
Bake cookie creations in a 325° to 350° oven.
Allow
1/2 hour baking time per 1/4 inch thickness of dough.
Average time is 1 hour.

title: easy salsa
directions: Place in blender and chop for 20 to 30 seconds. Store in refrigerator and use while fresh.

title: cream of wheat corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: orange scone
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yogurt and next 2 ingredients to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
(Dough will be sticky.)
With floured hands pat dough into 9-inch circle on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Cut dough into 10 wedges, cutting into but not through.
Sprinkle with remaining teaspoon of sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
(I use a 9-inch nonstick pan and spread a little butter or margarine on top before putting the sugar on.)

title: applesauce salad dressing
directions: In small bowl or jar stir all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Can be refrigerated 1 week.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Layer dried beef in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 325 degrees for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and crust.
Pour into unbaked crust; dot with butter.
Top with top crust.
Poke 3 or 4 holes in top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes until rhubarb is tender.

title: stuffed mushrooms parmigiana
directions: Remove mushroom stems; finely chop stems and reserve.
Drain caps on paper towel.
Melt butter in skillet; add onion, pepperoni, green pepper, garlic and mushroom stems.
Cook until vegetables are tender but not brown.
Add cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Stir in chicken broth.
Spoon stuffing into caps.
Place caps in baking pan with 1/4 inch water covering bottom of pan.
Bake uncovered at 325° about 25 minutes.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Delicious, try them for dinner tonight.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a medium saucepan. Blend in about 1/4 cup milk. Add remaining milk. Cook and stir over low heat until sauce boils and is thick and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla extract.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Just before serving, add corn chips and salad dressing.
If you add hamburger, it becomes a complete meal!

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt chocolate and butter together. Cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions; cook until soft.
Mix stems, crumbs, cottage cheese, salt and pepper together.
Add onions.
Fill caps; brown in skillet in butter for 3 minutes.
Broil mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: divinity
directions: Stir and mix well all ingredients except eggs and nuts.
Do not stir again after first mixing, while cooking.
Cook until forms a thread or reaches 234 degrees on candy thermometer.
Add 3-4 tablespoons of beaten egg whites.
Put syrup back on stove and cook to cracked ball stage or reaches 270 degrees.
Add egg whites and beat until looses its glossiness.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: california dip(low fat dip recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Chill overnight and serve with vegetables.

title: red cabbage - german style
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, saute onion in oil.
Add cabbage and turn until all cabbage is coated with oil and shiny.
Add vinegar, water or wine and diced apple.
Turn down heat; cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Before serving, add spices.
Mix cornstarch with enough water to dissolve.
Add to cabbage and mix well. Serves 4.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Season to taste.
Line bottom of 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole with cabbage.
Sprinkle rice over cabbage.
Spread meat and onion mixture on top.
Pour soup over all and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on kind of rice used (instant or fast cooking requires less time).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs until very light; gradually add sugar and beat again thoroughly.
Add melted butter, then nutmeg, soda dissolved.
Work in sufficient flour to make a dough.
Roll thin; cut out and bake in a quick oven at 400°.

title: apple coleslaw
directions: Toss cabbage, apple, celery,
raisins, and walnuts in large bowl.
Mix dressings, salt, and pepper in small bowl.
Add to cabbage mixture; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: festive pumpkin salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Stir in pumpkin, sour cream and lemon peel.
Mix well and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Chill until almost set.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in nuts and pour over pumpkin layer.
Chill until firm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate royale fondue
directions: Melt all chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add next 5 ingredients and stir until smooth and thickened.
Pour into fondue pot or chafing dish.
Serve with marshmallows, pound cake, pineapple, banana, apple and orange slices, strawberries or animal crackers.

title: nana's cheese balls
directions: Mix and form in small balls.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 25 balls.

title: eggplant hors d'oeuvre
directions: Cut eggplant lengthwise into halves and make several deep slits, do not pierce the skin.
Insert the garlic slivers into the cuts.
Lightly sprinkle the cut surface with salt and place the halves on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove eggplants, cool slightly and invert on paper towels.
As the eggplants finish cooling, squeeze them gently to eliminate any excess liquid.
Scrape the eggplant and garlic out of the skins into a small mixing bowl and mash.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in soy sauce, olive oil, chopped tomato and raisins. Refrigerate mixture overnight or for 2 to 3 days.
Just before serving, stir the mixture well.
Add more salt and pepper if needed.
Stir in toasted pine nuts.*
Cut pita bread into small triangles and serve with eggplant.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pack firmly in ungreased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and the nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over hot crust; top with 1 1/2 cups toffee bits.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture and remaining 1/2 cup chips over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup toffee bits.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 36 bars.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; bone and chop.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and line with tortilla shells.
Blend soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Pour half over shells.
Spread half over chicken.
Spread half over cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: calamondin marmalade
directions: Put cut calamondins in 1 1/2-quarts water and cook until tender (about 20 minutes).
Let stand overnight.
Put in strainer. Eliminate all seeds.
Put meat of fruit in blender, chop to desired size.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar to 1 cup of prepared fruit along with 2 cups water.
Cook in heavy pan, stirring most of the time, until it gels (218°).

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Cut brownies into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl:
half the brownies, 1 cup berries, 1 sliced banana and 1 tub chocolate topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and saute with meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then cut down to simmer.
Simmer at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesy cream corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and heat until cheese melts. Stir often.

title: grandma walker's carrot pudding
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Drain.
Mix with butter (mash with electric mixer or use potato masher).
Add diced onion.
Mix. Add 2/3 of the cheese.
Mix. Add 3/4 of the crackers.
Mix. Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and bubbly around edges (about 45 minutes).

title: *breasts of chicken magnifique
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
To butter in skillet, add the mushrooms and brown.
To the mushrooms, add soup, garlic, rosemary, thyme and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and mix well, then add the browned chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
(Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.)
Add cream and blend.
Heat for a couple of minutes, but do not boil.
Serve with rice and garnish with slivered almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray muffin tin with oil. Mix all ingredients. Fill 1/2 full muffin cups in muffin tin. Bake 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with vanilla wafer crumbs. Add butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Top with Eagle Brand milk.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain and cool.
Mix lettuce, cheese and tomatoes in serving bowl.
Just before serving, add meat and broken chips; toss with Catalina dressing.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in olives.
Break half of the spaghetti in roaster pan and 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers to make two layers and top with cheese.
Cover.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° and uncovered 20 minutes.

title: frozen blueberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and syrup from blueberries to boiling. Use to dissolve jello.
Allow to cool.
Mash bananas.
Add blueberries and bananas to jello mix.
Whip cream with a little sugar to serving consistency and blend into mixture.
Freeze in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish.
Serves 9.

title: no bake cookies (2)
directions: In sauce pan bring first 4 ingredients to a full boil. Boil 1 minute only. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a plastic container with a lid.
Allow the ingredients to marinate overnight or 2 or 3 days, if time permits, in the refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grape pie
directions: Separate
skins
from
seeds.
Cook
the
seed and pulp part. Keep
the skins in another pan and save.
Put seeds and pulp through food mill to take out seeds, then put the pulp in with the raw skins.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Moisten
edges
of	crust,	then put on top crust. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: take my heart pizza
directions: Preheat oven in accordance with instructions on refrigerated pizza dough, following cooking time also.
Assemble in order listed, beginning by pressing dough in pan and forming edges. Sprinkle sauce followed by meat and other ingredients.
Especially nice for birthdays, Valentine's day or showers.
As a main course, make 2 or 3 and serve with salad.
Serves 3 or 4 as appetizers.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Take one 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and melt margarine.
Dry chicken well and place in pan; roll in margarine to coat well. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon each of salt and pepper over chicken.
Dice onions and sprinkle over chicken with the rice.
Dilute the two cans of soup with 2 cans of water and pour slowly over chicken until all the rice is covered.

title: mother's no-cook divinity
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine dry frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large mixer bowl and beat on low speed, gradually blending in sugar.
Stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over; dry at least 12 hours.
Store candy in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen candies.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: higbee's muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar and egg yolks and beat again until fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients into shortening mixture alternately with milk, stirring just to moisten.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Divide batter among well-greased muffin pans.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
You can use yellow or white or 1 of each color of corn.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a large casserole dish with bacon.
Pour rice over bacon. Season chicken
with
spices
and
place
chicken over rice.
Mix together soup and 2/3 cup water.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Do
not
peek!!!! in the foil until cooking time is up.

title: pie crust for cream pies
directions: Melt margarine in pie plate.
Add powdered sugar.
Add flour. Stir in pie plate.
Take spoon and press around pie plate.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: apple fritters
