directions: Heat the milk until it is warm and add slowly to the beaten yolks of the eggs.
Add sugar.
Add the flour and the whites of the eggs.
Stir all together and add the apples.
Fry by the half cupful in hot lard.
(You might want to use shortening!)

title: apple spoon cake
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Layer apples in bottom.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
In separate bowl, mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add soft butter, milk and eggs; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press dough in a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Layer bacon, cheese, bell pepper and onion on top of dough.
Mix eggs and milk; pour on top.
Bake at 420° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine and honey in pan; when melted, add baking soda.
As soon as this mixture froths, add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread in jelly roll pan. Pat down mixture.
Bake about 25 minutes until brown.
Cut immediately.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: In a bowl, mash avocado with lemon juice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
In another bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip in 9 x 13-inch serving dish or large, clear, glass bowl.
Top with avocado mixture, then sour cream mixture.
Layer onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese over sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Put all ingredients into bowl and mix with hands.
Add extra flour until hands and bowl are clean.
Roll out on floured cloth and cut with cutter. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: spicy butter
directions: In a small bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Goes great on corn-on-cob.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove the bones and place in a baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth in a pot and bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the chicken.
Mix the vegetables in with the chicken.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; saute celery, onions and garlic in oil.
Add broccoli, cheese and soup; heat until bubbly.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: In a shallow casserole combine all ingredients except 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with the remaining onions and bake another 5 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onion, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: grapefruit and avocado salad
directions: Arrange grapefruit on four serving plates.
Arrange avocados on plates with grapefruit.
Spoon lime juice over each salad and salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Fill baking dish and completely cover with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger bundt
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make white sauce as follows:
In saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, then add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add 1 cup sharp cheese, grated.

title: winter soup
directions: Drain and chop tomatoes; reserve juice.
Dice potatoes and carrots.
Cut green and red peppers; set aside.

title: miami beach cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour bottoms of two 9-inch layer pans.
Melt 1/3 cup chocolate morsels.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Stir in walnuts and 2/3 cup chocolate morsels.
Set aside.
Combine flour with soda and salt. Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla extract.
At low speed, add dry ingredients
alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into pans.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool.
Beat cream with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Fill and frost sides with whipped cream, keeping layers top side up.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Microwave broccoli according to package directions.
Use 2 or 3 quart saucepan to saute onions in margarine.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk and heat with the onion mixture.
Add chunks of cheese and slowly melt cheese into mixture.
This makes 3 or 4 large bowls of soup and is so good with cornbread.
A dash of cayenne pepper is good.

title: this is so simple!
directions: Mix all together (except nuts) for 2 minutes with a spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Fold in 1 very full cup of chopped pecans or walnuts.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 1/2 hour. Remove from pan and continue to cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries. Add sugar and marshmallows. Cover and chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt. Fold in whipped cream. Chill.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Melt butter, add chopped seasonings and saute until tender. Remove from heat; add crabmeat and mix well.
Add egg and mix. Add enough bread crumbs to make mixture stick together.
Season well and stuff mixture into aluminum crab tins.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and a pat of butter, if desired.
Bake about 20 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together real good.
Roll into balls and put on broiler pan.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Put into crock-pot and pour Kraft barbecue sauce on and simmer for 2 hours.

title: hot dish
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and celery until browned.
Add seasoning.
Cook and drain the noodles.
Mix all ingredients; add 1/2 cup water.
Bake in buttered casserole; you can add any vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with soup. Add other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil vermicelli noodles and chicken together.
Meanwhile, grate cheese and chop onion.
Saute onion and stick of margarine in saucepan.
Pour margarine and onion in casserole dish.
Drain noodles and chicken.
Pour noodles into dish.
Dice or tear chicken and put in dish.
Pour in 1 can of cream of mushroom soup.
Stir. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle black pepper to taste. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: track soup
directions: Brown hamburger in small amount of cooking oil in frying pan. Place the browned hamburger and all the remaining ingredients in a 6-quart kettle.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, until vegetables are done.

title: praline  grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into four sections. Arrange in a jelly roll pan with edges touching. Melt butter in saucepan, stir in sugar and pecans. Bring to a boil. Cook 3 minutes stirring frequently. Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers. Bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool on wax paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together. Add pumpkin and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to above alternately with water. Place in greased bread pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: elegant clam chowder
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Place in a saucepan.
Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables.
Add enough water to barely cover and simmer, covered, over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: mamaw cake
directions: Mash 3 to 4 bananas (2 cups).
Sift dry ingredients and to it add undrained pineapple, oil, eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Mix until blended.
Don't beat, stir in nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in a moderate oven until done.
Can drizzle with a cream cheese glaze.

title: grape jelly
directions: In a large pan, put 5 cups juice.
Stir on medium-high heat and sprinkle in Sure-Jell.
When this starts to come to a rolling boil, slowly add sugar and stir until this comes to a rolling boil.
Stir at boil for 1 minute; skim off foam.
Remove from heat and fill jars.
Put wax on top in a few minutes and when cool, cover with lids.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add with buttermilk to dry ingredients; mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Add more flour if needed and knead about 1 minute.
Round out to 1/4 inch thick; cut and dip in melted margarine.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; cover and chill. Combine Italian dressing and mustard, stirring until blended. Pour over salad and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings (1 cup).

title: turkey curry
directions: Saute onion, celery and ground turkey (if not using cooked turkey).
Cool slightly.
Add cornstarch and mix well.
Add stock and cook until smooth and thickened.
Add tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder and pepper (then cooked turkey if not using fresh ground turkey).
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix well first 7 ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Put 1/2 the batter into pan.
Sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Put 1/2 the apples on top of butter and then put rest of batter on top of apples.
Top with rest of apples and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: children's finger paints
directions: Fill refillable insulated cup from Quick Trip with about 3/4 full of water.
Put into microwave and forget about it. (Actually I think it was the cup burning, but it turned the water brown, so my family tells me I can even burn water.)

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by box directions.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook the broccoli.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs in cranberry sauce
directions: Make meatballs, using bread crumbs.
Put meatballs in pot with 1 small can water, spaghetti sauce, tomato juice and cranberry sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, jello and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan. Add water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool mixture.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix and onion together. Spread on tortillas. Mix black olives, green chilies and pimentos together. Sprinkle over cream cheese. Roll up tortillas. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight. Slice and serve.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs gradually; then add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add the rest.
Put in 2 loaf pans or a dripping pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: orange gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco; add the eggs and beat hard.
Sift together soda, cream of tartar and flour and add to batter.
Add nuts, vanilla and orange slices.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Saut onion and bell pepper in butter. Brown ground beef and add onion, bell pepper and pizza sauce. Mix with cooked macaroni. Put 1/2 macaroni in Pyrex dish. Add 1/2 cheese. Add remaining macaroni and top with remaining cheese. Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven, until cheeses are melted.

title: hot sausages
directions: In skillet, saute onion and pepper.
In same skillet, brown sausages.
Pour sausages (drained), onion and pepper into crock-pot or slow cooker.
Pour tomato juice over sausage.
Add red pepper.
Let simmer on low for 2 to 4 hours.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Put rice in bottom of a casserole dish. Lightly season and brown chops in a skillet.
Put on top of rice. Mix consomme and water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add basil and thyme.
Pour into skillet with drippings and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over chops and rice.
Lay one slice each of onion, tomato and bell pepper on top of each chop.
Bake 1 hour, covered.

title: pickled beets
directions: Use medium to small beets for best results.
Cut stems at approximately 2 inches above beet.
Thoroughly wash beets without breaking skin of beets.
Put in large enamel pot.
Cook beets until tender, approximately 50 minutes.
Try not to let beets crack and bleed during cooking.
After cooking and while hot, place beets into cold water.
While still warm, the peelings will come off easily by squeezing with your hand.
Slice peeled beets and put in clean bowl.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
Brown ground chuck; drain.
Add corn, soup, tomatoes and macaroni.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with Mexican cornbread.
Top with Velveeta as you desire.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all four ingredients after crust together.
Save part of Cool Whip for the top of the pie, approximately 1 1/2 cups.
Mix with mixer until creamy.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape and chill.
Can be covered with pecans or the sliced beef.

title: chocolate pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pudding mix and baking mix in bowl. Mix together with wooden spoon.
Add oil and egg; mix together until mixture forms a ball.
Take a small spoonful of dough and shape it into a 1/2-inch ball.
Place ball on ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape rest of dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Place balls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press your thumb into middle of each ball to make a thumbprint.
Put peanut butter chips or candies in thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet with spatula.
Place on wire rack.

title: rolled chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Cut breasts into strips and roll.
Wrap ham around rolled breast.
Place rolls into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix all soup together and pour over chicken-ham rolls.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 1 hour.
Makes approximately 12 to 18 individual rolls.

title: guacamole
directions: In medium bowl, crush tomato with potato masher.
Peel avocados; halve crosswise and remove pits.
Slice avocados into crushed tomato.
Crush with tomato until well blended.
Add chile peppers, onions, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled, at least 1 hour. Prepare cauliflowerets, celery and carrot sticks.
Refrigerate in bowl of salted water until well chilled.
Serve guacamole, surrounded with drained vegetables, as an appetizer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: larry's german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9 inch) round cake pans.
Microwave chocolate and water in a large bowl on high 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time beating well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with butter milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites in another large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Gently stir into batter.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until cakes springs back when lightly touched.
Immediately loosen cake from pan.
Cool 15 minutes, and remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Spread frosting on top of each layer.
Makes 12 servings use coconut pecan filling frosting.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Boil salted chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and refrigerate broth until fat hardens on top. Discard fat.
Add onion and potatoes to broth and boil about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt, pepper, lima beans and chicken that has been removed from bones.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 1 hour or longer.
Add corn and continue cooking.
Blend together flour and margarine; add to stew in small amounts, stirring until slightly thickened.
If a thinner stew is desired, add more water.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.
Use 2 coffee scoops per cup of hot water.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch cubes and place half in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine onion, celery, chicken, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Spread over bread cubes.
Place remainder of bread cubes on top.

title: napa valley chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in roasting pan.
In saucepan combine remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Remove cover and turn chicken, skin side up.
Continue baking, uncovered, 1 hour longer, basting every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: basil stuffed chicken
directions: Heat broiler. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Slice each breast almost horizontally in half, but leaving one side attached.

title: low-fat dip for fruit
directions: Beat together cream cheese and Marshmallow Fluff.
Add cinnamon.
Stir well.
Let stand for 1/2 hour before serving. Serve with cut up fruit.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour with a little salt and pepper.
Brown meat; place in a slow cooker.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with noodles.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
To use, mix 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water or to suit your taste.

title: hot spinach salad(serve immediately)
directions: Place spinach in salad bowl.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Spoon bacon and drippings over spinach.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Pour over spinach and toss until leaves are well coated.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes, hard-cooked egg wedges and fresh mushrooms if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add the peeled and cleaned shrimp.
Add the wine, salt and pepper.
Simmer for five minutes.
You may also add a 1/2 can of chicken broth if you desire.

title: karis' kranberry salad
directions: Using a blender or food processor, make a relish of the first three ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: best refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Sprinkle yeast in the lukewarm water; stir until dissolved.
Combine with first mixture.
Add flour; blend well. Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours (can keep a week to 10 days in refrigerator and use as needed).
Roll dough into shapes or cut out.
Place in greased pan; let rise in warm place for 3 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dipped chocolates(no-cook fondant)
directions: Line 2 baking sheets with waxed paper; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, corn syrup, salt and extract.
Stir with a wooden spoon gradually working in powdered sugar.
When mixture is too stiff for a spoon, begin kneading as for bread dough.
When all the powdered sugar has been added, continue kneading until fondant is smooth.
Form into balls 3/4-inch in diameter and place on waxed paper trays.
Dip in tempered dipping chocolate or roll in nuts.
Press pecan half or candied cherry on each piece.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until thick, then slice apples.
Put in an uncooked pie crust or you may just pour over apples in a pie pan and cook.
You can sprinkle Sweet 'N Low over apples and mixture if you want.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: potato bread
directions: Boil and mash potato.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (can use potato water).
Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and mashed potato.
Add 2 cups flour and beat.
Add the rest of the flour. Use some flour on board and knead.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise.
Knead down once and place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 350°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook all ingredients, except coconut and Cool Whip, on top of stove until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell; cool.
Add Cool Whip to top.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: hot german potato and bean salad
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Brown bacon in skillet; drain on paper towel.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Saute onion in reserved bacon drippings in skillet until tender-crisp but not brown.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and caraway seed.
Add vinegar and reserved bean liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add beans and potatoes.
Cook just until heated through, stirring gently.
Spoon into serving dish.
Crumble bacon over top.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Set oven at 350°. Mix yellow cake mix as directed on package.
Mix together the Ricotta, eggs, sugar, lemon rind and vanilla.
Pour this mixture on top of cake batter.
Sprinkle the mixed sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot jalapeno marinade
directions: Place carrots in large bowl.
Cover with hot water (140° to 160°) and let stand about 30 minutes.
Drain and plunge into cold water.
Add a few ice cubes and let stand 15 to 20 minutes. Combine jalapenos with onion, oil, vinegar and salt.
Drain carrots and add to pepper mixture; cover and refrigerate. Marinade improves with age and will keep in refrigerator up to 4 months.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix together in order given except chocolate, nuts and chocolate chips.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube, angel or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).
Keep covered with foil.

title: potato pudding
directions: Peel potatoes and grate.
Mix with onion and flour.
Melt butter in a shallow one-quart baking dish.
Spoon potato mixture into baking dish.

title: granny peevy's cherry frost
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, coconut and nuts.
Add pie filling and pineapple and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour in bowl and top generously with coconut.
Refrigerate until ready to eat. Save some coconut for the top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and taco sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Put in blender the green pepper, tomato paste, butter, tomatoes, oregano leaves, sugar, onion, pepper, garlic and salt. Blend until onion and pepper are finely chopped.
Pour into saucepan.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes.

title: *russian tea*
directions: Mix together.
Add 2 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix and cook until thoroughly warmed.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let blend about 1 hour or more or overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, peppers, celery, carrots, cucumbers, etc.).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and margarine; cook for 5 minutes in heavy pan.
Use timer if possible to be sure of timing. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, chips, marshmallows and vanilla; stir.
Pan may be set in cold water to speed up process of cooling.
Continue beating until glossy appearance disappears. Pour at once into greased large pan or 2 smaller pans.
Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: aunt margaret's frozen buttermilk ice cream
directions: Mix all well; place in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: fiesta pork burritos
directions: Stir-fry pork strips in the canola oil with onion.
Stir in corn and toss with taco seasoning.
Warm tortillas.
Roll ingredients in tortillas when you've added toppings.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients together.
Let ingredients set for 5 minutes. Spoon batter into greased muffin pan liners.
Bake until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; place in greased dish.
Make sauce with the butter, flour, milk, cheese and seasonings.
Put almonds over broccoli; pour on sauce.
Crumble bacon on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: sweet and sour cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and place in large bowl.
It is optional to add cut tomato and chopped onion.
In a small bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, milk and pepper to taste.
Pour over cucumbers and stir.
Wait 5 to 10 minutes to serve.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries.
Cream the butter, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg whites; knead to mix.
Pinch a small portion of mixture and form a small ball around a cherry.
When all the cherries are covered with the sugar-butter mixture, melt the chocolate and paraffin together.
Dip the balls into the chocolate using hat pin or toothpick; set to drain on waxed paper.
After all are dipped, use a small spoon to drip chocolate on top to cover toothpick hole.

title: zucchini christmas bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream oleo until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spread evenly on well-greased cookie sheet or 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread frosting over warm layer and cut in squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown
beef
until crumbly.
Stir in dry taco mix.
Add tomatoes and corn.	Bring to a soft boil, stirring frequently. Pour
into	a
2 quart casserole dish.
Carefully top with the corn
bread mix which has been prepared to bake.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.	Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until thick.
Stir in zucchini.
(I do not peel as it gives more color.)
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to original mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: spaghetti carbonaro
directions: Hard-cook eggs.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove and drain on absorbent paper.
Take out all but one tablespoon bacon fat; saute onions and green peppers in fat until golden.
Add raisins and both cans of spaghetti and meat balls.
Cover and simmer for five minutes.
Shell and dice hard-cooked eggs.
Toss spinach with cheese and salt.
Arrange spaghetti mixture in center of platter.
Arrange spinach around outside of platter. Garnish with chopped eggs.
Serves four to six.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain and crumble. In a separate pan, combine remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Add to meat and simmer for 15 minutes. Stir to keep from sticking. Serves 20.

title: dairy state fudge
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; set aside.
In double boiler, melt butter.
Add almond bark; heat and stir until melted and smooth.
Pour over cream cheese; beat until smooth and glossy, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: yankee seashell salad
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine macaroni, celery, carrots, peas, parsley and green onions.
Combine oil, lemon juice, vinegar, dill weed, celery seed and salt in a screw top jar and shake well. Pour over macaroni mixture; toss well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Toss again.
Break salmon into large pieces.
Fold into macaroni mixture.
Spoon salad into salad bowl lined with salad greens.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Thoroughly heat beans
in
saucepan.
In separate small pan, pour 1 cup green
bean
juice.
Add mushroom soup, garlic salt and black pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
When soup mixture is hot, stir in milk, water
chestnuts,
cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Heat. Drain the
green
beans
and
combine
the
two mixtures.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 can onion rings and
almonds and pimiento, if desired, for color.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage hamburger quiche
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onions on medium heat.
Drain. Add celery, garlic, green peppers and eggs.
Stir.
Add flour and shredded cheese.
Stir.
Add milk.
Stir until ingredients are mixed together.
Divide the mixture evenly into 2 pie shells, unbaked.
Pies are done when crusts are brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruitcake cookie "jewels"
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs, beating until fluffy.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour mixture.
Add nuts, fruit and raisins.
Chill dough for several hours, then drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Top each cookie with a cherry half.
Bake at 375° (preheated) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: spinach balls
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze out water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Form balls using large tablespoon.
Bake on sprayed cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mashed potatoes
directions: Mix
together
first 5 ingredients by hand.
Separately mix together
remaining ingredients for stuffing.
On floured board, reshape potato mixture into 6 to 7 potato shapes.
Make a "trench" in potato.
Stuff.
Pinch to close.
Roll on board to cylinder (potato) shape.
Beat 2 eggs.
Have toasted bread crumbs ready. Roll
potatoes
in
egg
and then bread crumbs. Reform if necessary.
Deep fry in frypan.
Turn.
Brown well. Drain.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork.
Mix together water, sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork, then add bell pepper and cherries and let simmer for 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: key lime bars
directions: Combine the flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in the margarine.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden in color.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter.
Beat eggs.
Add mixed dry ingredients and eggs, then milk and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Then add:
oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper (teaspoon size).

title: crockpot macaroni cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Place in crockpot.
Add oleo, milks and cheese.
Stir.
Put some of the cheese on top. Cook 3 hours on high.
Do not stir before serving.
Delicious.

title: almond squares
directions: Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat.
Cover; refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours until dough is firm enough to handle.
Remove wrappers from chocolate kisses. Heat oven to 375°.
Use 1 tablespoon dough.
Shape it around kiss to make ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, set but not brown.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.

title: potato bake
directions: Place potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix with potatoes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and simmer.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, egg and Mozzarella.
Spread sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread a large spoonful of mixture on uncooked lasagna noodles.
Turn upside-down on sauce.
Continue to layer until you finish with sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Top with more Mozzarella and bake 30 minutes more.

title: mexican rice
directions: Add onion, garlic and rice to hot oil in heavy saucepan.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Stir in a mixture of chili powder and salt.
Add water; stir. Cover tightly.
Bring to boiling and simmer until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Combine beaten egg, sugar and shortening; add milk.
Mix flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Combine the liquid and dry ingredients, stirring only until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness on floured board or counter.
Fry doughnuts in Crisco heated to 365°.
Will be brown in 60 seconds.

title: dog droppings
directions: Cream powdered sugar and butter or margarine (softened).
Add peanut butter.
Spoon in Rice Krispies and mix all together.
Form into balls.

title: chicken livers with mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle livers with salt and half the flour to coat.
Heat butter in large skillet; add liver, onion and mushrooms and saute 5 or 6 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove from skillet.
Blend remaining flour into fat in skillet until smooth, then gradually add soup and milk.
Add pepper to taste.
Cook gently 4 or 5 minutes, stirring to keep smooth.
When thickened, stir livers into the sauce.
Serve on cheese waffles or toast.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Best served on cornbread pancakes.
Serves 6.

title: aunt lena's molasses cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, shortening and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Do not flatten!
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375 for 12-15 minutes.

title: crazy coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender for 1 minute on blend. Grease and flour 10-inch pie plate.
Pour ingredients into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Need a 5-cup blender or larger.)

title: jello cold cake
directions: Prepare
cake
mix as directed on box and bake in sheet pan. When
done, punch holes in cake.
Mix Jell-O as directed on
box. Pour
Jell-O over cake.
Place in refrigerator overnight
or until Jell-O sets.	Jell-O will go to the bottom of the pan.
Use a hot knife when cutting.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: frozen peaches and cream
directions: Combine vanilla wafers with butter, blending well.
Pat evenly over sides and bottom of an 8-inch baking dish.
Chill.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in plastic bag.
Add margarine.
Add sugar and juice; mix well.
Make small balls; roll in sugar or coconut.

title: never fail chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a slow boil.
Stir until mixed well.

title: green glow punch
directions: Combine concentrates and water in a large, nonmetal pitcher or punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.
Stir to blend.
A scoop of lime sherbet may be added.
Makes 25 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into ball and roll in parsley and nuts.
This also freezes well.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese; mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Roll into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Freeze.
While frozen, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Simmer one hour on low heat. French-style green beans could be added, if desired.
Double if needed.
Makes 2 servings.

title: alice's lemon bars(absolutely divine!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions and chill.
Mix all other ingredients. Dip chilled onions in batter and fry in hot cooking oil.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Drop in eggs and beat. Add flour, salt, soda, nuts, vanilla, raisins and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add paprika, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and coat well.
Add water.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to sauce and heat to thicken, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.

title: easy cookie recipe
directions: *If you use Crisco or shortening, cutout cookies will lose their shape.

title: vegetable soup mixture
directions: Boil butter beans and tomatoes for 30 to 45 minutes (water may be added if needed).
Add rest of ingredients and cook 45 minutes. Seal in jars or put in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Put the potatoes, onion and sausage into casserole.
Add the soup.
A can of peas may be added.
Add the salt, pepper, parsley and other spices, if desired.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Can also use ham, chicken or turkey.

title: pineapple squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove the seeds.
Fill the cavity with the pineapple.
Place in a baking dish.
Cover and bake at 450° until you can easily pierce the squash with a fork.
It takes about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
A great dip for nacho chips.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat.
Cut peppers into small pieces.
Cut onion into small pieces.
Drain grease from meat.
Add remaining ingredients to meat.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add orange slices and pineapple.
Mix in the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mom's hot clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for about 4 minutes, mixing about every minute or so.
(Can also be done in double boiler, if preferred.)
Cook only until heated through.
Serve hot with potato chips.

title: moist banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas; beat well.
Stir in by spoon the bananas six or seven times.
(Do not use a mixer for the bananas.)
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: south american potato soup
directions: Cook chicken in a large cooker until fully cooked.
Cool and debone.
Discard and put back into broth.
Peel and dice potatoes. Place into broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until light.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut into bars while warm. Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 18 bars.

title: cherry cloud cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on the box, substituting applesauce for the oil and 2 egg whites for every egg called for. Bake in 2 round pans as package directs.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool and chill.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Spread over top of cakes.
Spoon on the pie filling over the top. Keep refrigerated.

title: malcalmation cake
directions: Mix well and bake.
